WEBVTT

00:01.088 --> 00:03.003
[ominous music]

00:03.046 --> 00:12.969
♪ ♪

00:13.013 --> 00:15.798
[Annie]
Natalie, come back here.

00:15.841 --> 00:17.147
Natalie!

00:17.191 --> 00:27.243
♪ ♪

00:27.244 --> 00:32.641
♪ ♪

00:32.683 --> 00:35.122
Natalie?

00:35.165 --> 00:38.473
Where are you, honey?

00:38.516 --> 00:41.824
Are you in here?

00:41.867 --> 00:44.827
You can come out now.

00:44.870 --> 00:46.611
It's all right.

00:46.655 --> 00:48.396
Mommy's here.

00:48.439 --> 00:54.315
♪ ♪

00:54.358 --> 00:55.620
[screams]

00:55.664 --> 00:57.796
[gasps]

00:57.840 --> 00:58.971
Huh?

01:01.061 --> 01:03.237
[Caroline]
Natalie!

01:03.280 --> 01:05.021
Oh my God.

01:05.065 --> 01:06.631
I've been looking everywhere
for you, honey.

01:06.675 --> 01:08.111
I'm sorry.

01:08.155 --> 01:09.721
Oh, no, no, no, it's okay, baby.

01:09.765 --> 01:11.941
I dreamt about her again.

01:11.984 --> 01:13.812
I know, I know, it's okay.

01:13.856 --> 01:15.292
Okay, let's get you home, okay?

01:15.336 --> 01:18.643
- Yeah.
- Yeah? Okay, come on.

01:18.687 --> 01:21.472
[soft music]

01:21.516 --> 01:29.698
♪ ♪

01:29.741 --> 01:31.265
[TV news anchor]
For more on
the Annie Weaver story,

01:31.308 --> 01:34.703
we take you to our correspondent
in San Marcos, California,

01:34.746 --> 01:37.793
- Lisa Collins. Lisa?
- Thanks, David.

01:37.836 --> 01:40.143
I'm here at the San Marcos
State Prison,

01:40.187 --> 01:43.146
where a last-minute appeal
for a stay of execution

01:43.190 --> 01:45.235
of Annie Weaver has failed.

01:45.279 --> 01:48.108
Weaver was charged with
the brutal double homicide

01:48.151 --> 01:51.154
of Frank and Lucy Miller
eight years ago,

01:51.198 --> 01:53.504
a suburban couple
who had been renting a room

01:53.548 --> 01:56.116
in Weaver's Ridgeside home.

01:56.159 --> 01:58.814
The weapon used
to murder the couple

01:58.857 --> 02:02.078
earned Weaver the nickname
"Weaver the Cleaver Killer."

02:02.122 --> 02:04.167
Weaver's trial took
a dramatic turn

02:04.211 --> 02:06.038
when her own daughter,

02:06.082 --> 02:07.997
Natalie Weaver, then age 10,

02:08.039 --> 02:09.824
testified against her.

02:09.868 --> 02:13.785
Weaver is set to be executed
one month from today,

02:13.829 --> 02:16.962
though her legal team maintains
her innocence and vows...

02:17.006 --> 02:18.486
[clicks TV off]

02:18.529 --> 02:20.401
You don't have to do that.

02:20.444 --> 02:21.532
Do what?

02:21.576 --> 02:23.795
I make breakfast every morning.

02:23.839 --> 02:26.363
Turn off the TV
just because it's about her.

02:26.407 --> 02:27.495
[Caroline]
Well, you shouldn't listen

02:27.538 --> 02:28.757
to that stuff.

02:28.800 --> 02:30.759
[Natalie]
It's fine.

02:30.802 --> 02:33.240
I'm used to it.

02:33.283 --> 02:34.763
You don't have to protect me.

02:34.806 --> 02:36.547
I'm not a child anymore.

02:36.591 --> 02:38.549
[Caroline]
Trust me, I know.

02:38.593 --> 02:40.856
Your father
would be really proud

02:40.899 --> 02:43.815
of the amazing young woman
you've become.

02:43.859 --> 02:46.209
Did you get any sleep
last night?

02:46.253 --> 02:48.080
♪ ♪

02:48.124 --> 02:49.604
[inhales deeply]

02:49.647 --> 02:51.606
The nightmares will stop.

02:51.649 --> 02:53.521
Just give it time.

02:53.564 --> 02:56.654
They're getting worse.

02:56.698 --> 02:58.308
My mom...

02:58.352 --> 02:59.962
am I like her?

03:00.005 --> 03:02.225
No.

03:02.269 --> 03:04.662
Listen, honey.

03:04.706 --> 03:07.796
I have known you
your entire life,

03:07.839 --> 03:11.365
and you are nothing like her.

03:11.408 --> 03:13.062
Thanks.

03:13.105 --> 03:14.933
I'll talk to Dr. Welk
about it later.

03:14.977 --> 03:16.892
[Caroline]
Good.

03:16.935 --> 03:18.241
You working today?

03:18.285 --> 03:21.549
Yeah. Four to eight.

03:21.592 --> 03:23.072
I gotta go.

03:23.115 --> 03:27.772
♪ ♪

03:27.816 --> 03:30.558
[suspenseful music]

03:30.601 --> 03:32.777
♪ ♪

03:32.821 --> 03:35.258
[indiscernible chatter,
laughter]

03:35.302 --> 03:43.179
♪ ♪

03:43.223 --> 03:45.529
[Geoff]
Here, let me.

03:45.573 --> 03:47.531
♪ ♪

03:47.575 --> 03:49.446
- Jerks.
- Why bother?

03:49.490 --> 03:51.622
They'll just post them
back up tomorrow.

03:51.666 --> 03:53.668
[laughter]

03:55.757 --> 03:58.020
[Kent]
Little murder baby.

03:58.063 --> 04:00.283
- You okay?
- Sure.

04:00.327 --> 04:02.851
- Why wouldn't I be?
- Watch this. Hey, Weaver!

04:02.894 --> 04:04.766
Just wanna make sure
you got the note I left.

04:04.809 --> 04:06.420
I don't wanna have to worry
about a domestic incident

04:06.463 --> 04:08.160
with a kitchen knife
in home ec later.

04:08.204 --> 04:10.293
[laughter]

04:10.337 --> 04:12.469
- [locker door slams]
- Hey, I'm curious.

04:12.513 --> 04:14.428
Do they send you
the electric bill

04:14.471 --> 04:17.952
for her execution, or do we
all get to chip in on that?

04:17.995 --> 04:20.303
[Geoff]
What is your malfunction,
seriously?

04:20.346 --> 04:23.393
[Kent]
Wow. Look who found a pair.

04:23.437 --> 04:26.527
They drop this morning, Geoff?

04:26.570 --> 04:29.181
[Geoff]
Leave her alone.

04:29.225 --> 04:31.053
[Kent]
You can't actually
be friends with her.

04:31.096 --> 04:32.272
You're just doing it
so she doesn't put you

04:32.315 --> 04:34.012
on a kill list, right?

04:34.056 --> 04:35.536
[Geoff]
You're an ass.

04:35.579 --> 04:37.015
[slam]

04:37.059 --> 04:39.583
[Kent]
Come on! Do you wanna go?

04:39.627 --> 04:40.932
[Natalie]
Hey, Kent!

04:40.976 --> 04:43.370
[sharp crack, gasping]

04:43.413 --> 04:45.937
[principal]
Both of you, my office, now!

04:45.981 --> 04:49.289
♪ ♪

04:49.332 --> 04:51.160
[Natalie]
I just couldn't take it anymore.

04:51.203 --> 04:53.423
And wham, I hit him.

04:53.467 --> 04:57.601
Suspended for two days,
three days of detention.

04:57.645 --> 05:01.039
I hardly think your aunt
is gonna be happy about that.

05:01.083 --> 05:02.954
I know.

05:02.998 --> 05:05.392
I just... I'd had it.

05:05.435 --> 05:07.176
I don't know what came over me.

05:07.219 --> 05:09.091
Something inside me
just snapped.

05:09.134 --> 05:10.962
[Dr. Welk]
Hm.

05:11.006 --> 05:12.703
[Natalie]
Maybe it's a side effect
of the medication?

05:12.747 --> 05:15.402
You mean,
sudden fits of violence?

05:15.445 --> 05:16.925
No.

05:16.968 --> 05:19.841
Not in my experience.

05:19.884 --> 05:21.799
Speaking of which,

05:21.843 --> 05:24.585
I don't think the medication
you gave me is working.

05:24.628 --> 05:27.457
The sleepwalking
is more common now.

05:27.501 --> 05:29.764
Mm-hm, it takes a while
to get into your system.

05:29.807 --> 05:31.679
Gotta give it more time.

05:31.722 --> 05:33.289
And the dreams?

05:33.333 --> 05:34.812
I'm having them
all the time now.

05:34.856 --> 05:36.423
I'm not surprised.

05:36.466 --> 05:38.381
Clearly, they're being
triggered by your mother

05:38.425 --> 05:41.210
being in the news lately,
it's called a stressor event.

05:41.253 --> 05:42.559
In cases like yours,

05:42.603 --> 05:45.257
trauma can lie dormant
for years.

05:45.301 --> 05:48.522
And then suddenly,
it's drawn to the surface.

05:48.565 --> 05:52.787
[Natalie]
Great. Lucky me.

05:52.830 --> 05:56.747
[Dr. Welk]
Maybe you should
see yourself as lucky.

05:56.791 --> 05:58.706
Rather than looking at
these events as a burden,

05:58.749 --> 06:01.796
what if you saw them
from another perspective,

06:01.839 --> 06:04.407
looked at them as a way to heal?

06:04.451 --> 06:07.062
Let them lead you
to resolve these issues

06:07.105 --> 06:08.977
once and for all.

06:09.020 --> 06:11.371
[Natalie]
How?

06:11.414 --> 06:13.634
You've never gone to visit her?

06:15.331 --> 06:17.246
I haven't seen her
in eight years.

06:17.289 --> 06:20.249
Since the trial.

06:20.292 --> 06:26.908
[Dr. Welk]
It might be a good idea
to go see her.

06:26.951 --> 06:29.258
In person?

06:29.301 --> 06:31.826
I wouldn't even
know what to say.

06:31.869 --> 06:33.218
Whatever you need to.

06:33.262 --> 06:35.482
It might be the best way
to get answers,

06:35.525 --> 06:37.658
certainly to get closure.

06:37.701 --> 06:39.616
[soft music]

06:39.660 --> 06:41.226
She's your mother.

06:41.270 --> 06:43.359
At the very least,

06:43.403 --> 06:45.840
it will give you
a chance to say goodbye.

06:45.883 --> 06:50.192
♪ ♪

06:50.235 --> 06:52.237
[Caroline]
Suspended for two days.

06:52.281 --> 06:53.935
What are you gonna do
while I'm at the office?

06:53.978 --> 06:56.372
How are you gonna make up
that schoolwork, huh?

06:56.416 --> 06:59.201
[Natalie]
Geoff said he'd bring me
whatever I missed.

06:59.244 --> 07:00.681
And I already talked to Owen
about doing

07:00.724 --> 07:02.160
extra shifts at the store.

07:02.204 --> 07:04.162
I'll keep busy.

07:04.206 --> 07:05.599
[sighs]

07:05.642 --> 07:07.470
We're lucky
he didn't press charges.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.080
I couldn't help it!

07:09.124 --> 07:11.692
With all the looks
and whispers behind my back.

07:11.735 --> 07:14.999
Kent just pushed me
over the edge.

07:15.043 --> 07:17.524
I know, baby.

07:17.567 --> 07:19.874
But you're just gonna have
to be a little bit more careful

07:19.917 --> 07:24.052
right now with everything
in the news.

07:24.095 --> 07:26.489
It's gonna blow over when...

07:30.145 --> 07:32.756
Just no more punching people,
understood?

07:32.800 --> 07:34.584
Understood.

07:34.628 --> 07:37.326
But you have to agree.

07:37.369 --> 07:41.417
He deserved it, right?

07:41.461 --> 07:45.116
Eat, before you further
incriminate yourself.

07:45.160 --> 07:48.293
[ominous music]

07:48.337 --> 07:53.515
♪ ♪

07:53.516 --> 07:58.347
♪ ♪

08:14.885 --> 08:16.844
[buzzer sounding]

08:16.887 --> 08:21.022
♪ ♪

08:21.065 --> 08:24.068
[buzzing, beep]

08:26.027 --> 08:27.724
[footsteps]

08:27.768 --> 08:29.509
[prison official]
Weaver.

08:29.552 --> 08:31.554
You got a visitor.

08:31.598 --> 08:33.251
[indistinct chatter]

08:33.294 --> 08:35.645
No physical contact is allowed.

08:35.688 --> 08:38.039
That includes
displays of affection.

08:38.082 --> 08:40.083
Is that clear?

08:40.128 --> 08:41.650
- Is that clear?
- Yes.

08:44.654 --> 08:47.483
[prison official]
She hasn't gotten too many
visitors over the years.

08:49.877 --> 08:53.228
[buzzing, beep]

08:53.271 --> 08:55.404
[gasps]
Natalie!

08:55.447 --> 08:57.145
[prison official]
Remain seated.

08:59.016 --> 09:01.149
Baby!

09:01.192 --> 09:03.238
I'm so happy to see you.

09:05.936 --> 09:08.112
You have no idea
how much I've missed you.

09:08.156 --> 09:10.811
I thought that I would
never see you again.

09:10.854 --> 09:12.987
I mean, I dreamt about it.

09:13.030 --> 09:15.598
I used to hope every day
that you would come see me,

09:15.642 --> 09:17.905
but then after all the years,
I just lost faith.

09:17.948 --> 09:20.429
I'm sorry.

09:20.472 --> 09:23.258
I guess I'm just
a slobbering mess.

09:23.301 --> 09:25.042
It's okay.

09:25.086 --> 09:28.176
I'm sorry I didn't visit before.

09:28.219 --> 09:30.657
[Annie]
No, I understand.

09:30.700 --> 09:35.096
Did, um...
did Caroline bring you here?

09:35.139 --> 09:39.100
No. She doesn't know.

09:39.143 --> 09:43.887
Right. Well, that's
probably for the better.

09:43.931 --> 09:49.371
I can't even imagine how
difficult this has been for you.

09:49.414 --> 09:51.025
Why did you do it?

09:51.068 --> 09:53.244
[dramatic music]

09:53.288 --> 09:56.291
I need to know.

09:56.334 --> 09:57.771
You don't remember?

09:57.814 --> 10:00.208
♪ ♪

10:00.251 --> 10:02.210
Good.

10:02.253 --> 10:04.995
You were so young,
I mean, just a little girl,

10:05.039 --> 10:07.998
and I was there to protect you.

10:08.042 --> 10:09.652
What does that mean?

10:09.696 --> 10:12.263
♪ ♪

10:12.307 --> 10:14.526
It's best that
we don't talk about it.

10:14.570 --> 10:17.878
It's why I never blamed you
for any of it.

10:17.921 --> 10:20.010
For... for what you said in court,

10:20.054 --> 10:23.797
- and not writing back.
- What?

10:23.840 --> 10:26.713
Well, the letters I sent.

10:26.756 --> 10:28.149
I just wanted you to know
I was thinking about you

10:28.192 --> 10:29.846
every day.

10:29.890 --> 10:32.283
I never got any letters.

10:32.327 --> 10:34.721
I sent one a week!

10:34.764 --> 10:36.766
For years!

10:36.810 --> 10:38.376
And eventually, when I accepted

10:38.420 --> 10:40.291
that you weren't
gonna write back,

10:40.335 --> 10:41.597
I stopped mailing them,

10:41.641 --> 10:43.338
but I never stopped
writing them.

10:43.381 --> 10:45.557
They're still in my cell.

10:45.601 --> 10:49.953
I just wanted you to know
my side.

10:49.997 --> 10:52.434
That I would never leave you,

10:52.477 --> 10:56.307
and I would never
stop loving you.

10:56.351 --> 10:58.135
And I could never hurt anyone.

10:58.179 --> 11:02.096
♪ ♪

11:02.139 --> 11:03.880
[Natalie]
Do you know, does she...

11:03.924 --> 11:06.535
does my mom write
a lot of letters?

11:06.578 --> 11:08.145
[prison official]
Writes 'em, gets 'em.

11:08.189 --> 11:09.843
[chuckles]

11:09.886 --> 11:11.540
Most of these women
have pen pals.

11:11.583 --> 11:13.455
Some even come visit.

11:13.498 --> 11:16.719
A few are just lonely,
looking for love, but...

11:16.763 --> 11:18.460
most of the time, it's sickos

11:18.503 --> 11:20.723
just wanna hear
about what they did.

11:20.767 --> 11:24.031
[Natalie]
Has she ever said anything
about the murders?

11:24.074 --> 11:25.728
[prison official]
What they all say.

11:25.772 --> 11:27.425
"I didn't do it."

11:27.469 --> 11:29.558
[tense music]

11:29.601 --> 11:37.131
♪ ♪

11:37.174 --> 11:39.742
Nat! I'm home!

11:39.786 --> 11:46.270
♪ ♪

11:46.314 --> 11:47.707
What are you doing?

11:47.750 --> 11:50.057
- Where are they?
- Where are what?

11:50.100 --> 11:53.321
The letters!
The ones Annie sent me!

11:53.364 --> 11:54.888
There are no letters.

11:54.931 --> 11:58.456
You're lying! She said
she sent one every week.

11:58.500 --> 12:01.459
- You went to see her?
- Give them to me, they're mine.

12:01.503 --> 12:03.157
I have a right to read them!

12:03.200 --> 12:04.767
Why would you do that?

12:04.811 --> 12:07.639
- I have told you...
- Because she's my mother.

12:07.683 --> 12:08.902
Now, where are they?

12:08.945 --> 12:11.208
♪ ♪

12:11.252 --> 12:12.732
They're gone.

12:12.775 --> 12:15.038
[soft music]

12:15.082 --> 12:16.257
I burned them.

12:16.300 --> 12:19.477
♪ ♪

12:19.521 --> 12:22.742
Why?

12:22.785 --> 12:26.528
Because they would have only
caused you more pain.

12:26.571 --> 12:27.834
And you had already experienced

12:27.877 --> 12:30.010
so much of that already.

12:30.053 --> 12:32.708
I've managed to keep you
safe from her

12:32.752 --> 12:34.928
for the last eight years.

12:34.971 --> 12:38.540
She's evil, Natalie.

12:38.583 --> 12:40.150
You didn't know her,
you were just a child,

12:40.194 --> 12:41.935
but I did,

12:41.978 --> 12:45.112
even before
she married your father.

12:45.155 --> 12:46.983
I knew what she was like.

12:47.027 --> 12:49.986
She was manipulative
and conniving,

12:50.030 --> 12:52.772
always seeming so innocent.

12:52.815 --> 12:54.512
You didn't see her.

12:54.556 --> 12:56.732
She wasn't like that at all!

12:56.776 --> 12:58.995
Yes, she is,
and people don't change,

12:59.039 --> 13:00.475
not people like her.

13:00.518 --> 13:01.998
You're wrong.

13:02.042 --> 13:05.088
And you had no right
to throw them out!

13:05.132 --> 13:19.450
♪ ♪

13:21.888 --> 13:24.673
- Natalie?
- Go away.

13:28.111 --> 13:31.767
I'm sorry you had to find out
this way.

13:31.811 --> 13:34.944
[mournful music]

13:34.988 --> 13:45.040
♪ ♪

13:45.041 --> 13:54.529
♪ ♪

13:54.572 --> 13:56.618
[Natalie]
So Aunt Caroline was pissed,

13:56.661 --> 13:59.490
not that I care, since
she lied to me for years.

13:59.534 --> 14:03.451
I'm... I'm sure her intentions
were good.

14:03.494 --> 14:05.627
All I can think about
is how my mom is nothing

14:05.670 --> 14:10.893
like you hear on TV,
or like I remember.

14:10.937 --> 14:15.115
She was meek, almost broken.

14:15.158 --> 14:18.074
Nothing like the monster
everyone claims.

14:18.118 --> 14:20.990
How does that make you feel?

14:21.034 --> 14:23.906
Relieved.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.735
But also unsure.

14:26.778 --> 14:29.477
Unsure of what?

14:29.520 --> 14:31.609
If she's not who they said,

14:31.653 --> 14:34.438
what if I got it wrong
back then?

14:34.482 --> 14:38.181
What if what I said in court
wasn't true,

14:38.225 --> 14:40.009
and I was just believing
all the stories

14:40.053 --> 14:42.446
people were telling me?

14:42.490 --> 14:46.624
That would be
a very big thing to admit.

14:46.668 --> 14:49.366
I just wish I could remember
what happened.

14:49.410 --> 14:51.803
I get pieces, but never
the whole picture.

14:51.847 --> 14:54.154
Look, if you really
want to remember,

14:54.197 --> 14:56.373
you may need to go back there.

14:56.417 --> 14:58.158
Back to the house?

14:58.201 --> 15:00.334
I haven't been there
since that night.

15:00.377 --> 15:01.944
I understand,
but revisiting the house

15:01.988 --> 15:04.555
may be exactly what you need

15:04.599 --> 15:06.906
to trigger your memories.

15:06.949 --> 15:09.821
[tense music]

15:09.865 --> 15:14.348
♪ ♪

15:15.915 --> 15:19.005
- Hi.
- How is exile going?

15:19.048 --> 15:21.050
- You bored yet?
- I've been keeping busy.

15:21.094 --> 15:23.966
[Geoff]
Anything beats
fourth-period trig.

15:24.010 --> 15:26.229
Speaking of which,
here is the homework

15:26.273 --> 15:29.145
- you missed.
- Thanks.

15:29.189 --> 15:31.060
[Geoff]
Everyone at school's
talking about you,

15:31.104 --> 15:33.758
like you're this total badass.

15:33.802 --> 15:36.370
[Natalie]
Right. That's exactly
how I see myself.

15:36.413 --> 15:37.980
[laughter]

15:38.024 --> 15:40.765
[Kent]
Oh my God, it's perfect.

15:40.809 --> 15:45.335
It's got the blood
and everything, geez.

15:45.379 --> 15:48.860
- Can I help you?
- Just browsing.

15:48.904 --> 15:51.298
Looking for ideas for Halloween.

15:51.341 --> 15:54.431
Maybe I'll go as "Weaver
the Cleaver Killer" this year.

15:54.475 --> 15:57.217
Die, die, die, die, die!

15:57.260 --> 16:00.829
Want me to help you
find a dress?

16:00.872 --> 16:03.005
[Kent]
Think you can get your mom
to sign this for me?

16:03.049 --> 16:04.746
Make it worth something
before she, uh...

16:04.789 --> 16:06.574
[gurgling noises]

16:06.617 --> 16:08.837
[Geoff]
Lay off, douchebag.

16:08.880 --> 16:10.621
[Kent]
What are you, Natalie's
little lapdog or something?

16:10.665 --> 16:13.233
Arf, arf, arf, arf!

16:13.276 --> 16:15.148
Maybe you'd like to get
your ass kicked again,

16:15.191 --> 16:17.063
- or worse.
- Uh-oh.

16:17.106 --> 16:19.456
Looks like someone's
gonna go psycho!

16:19.500 --> 16:21.241
♪ ♪

16:21.284 --> 16:23.025
Like mother, like daughter,
I guess.

16:23.069 --> 16:26.246
- Is there a problem?
- Actually, there is.

16:26.289 --> 16:27.943
This employee's threatening me.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.597
She knocked that toy
outta my hand.

16:29.640 --> 16:31.120
Yeah, I saw what you were doing.

16:31.164 --> 16:33.731
I think it's best if you leave.

16:33.775 --> 16:35.603
[Kent]
I thought the customer
was always right.

16:35.646 --> 16:37.692
That's true, but in order
to be a customer,

16:37.735 --> 16:39.259
you need to buy something.

16:39.302 --> 16:40.825
[Kent]
No thanks.

16:40.869 --> 16:42.697
I don't want any of this
cheap junk anyway.

16:42.740 --> 16:46.614
Besides, Annie Weaver'll be
old news in a couple weeks.

16:46.657 --> 16:49.356
Let's go.

16:49.399 --> 16:51.097
- Bye, loser.
- Thank you.

16:51.140 --> 16:52.533
Save it.

16:52.576 --> 16:54.796
Like I said,
I heard the whole thing.

16:54.839 --> 16:57.929
Threatening customers
is bad business.

16:57.973 --> 17:00.193
Next time, rise above.

17:00.236 --> 17:01.846
Sorry.

17:01.890 --> 17:04.719
[eerie music]

17:04.762 --> 17:09.940
♪ ♪

17:09.941 --> 17:14.771
♪ ♪

17:39.710 --> 17:41.147
[Kent]
Who are you?

17:41.190 --> 17:42.713
Get away from me!

17:42.757 --> 17:44.498
Leave me alone!

17:44.541 --> 17:47.109
[dramatic music]

17:47.153 --> 18:01.819
♪ ♪

18:01.863 --> 18:03.082
[exclaims]

18:03.125 --> 18:04.692
[sharp thwack]

18:04.735 --> 18:10.219
♪ ♪

18:10.263 --> 18:12.047
[Annie, in ghostly echo]
Natalie?

18:12.091 --> 18:15.398
You can come out now.

18:15.442 --> 18:16.921
[gasps]

18:16.965 --> 18:19.141
Oh, don't cry, baby!

18:19.185 --> 18:21.274
Everything's gonna be okay!

18:21.317 --> 18:23.711
♪ ♪

18:23.754 --> 18:25.713
Just take my hand.

18:25.756 --> 18:36.985
♪ ♪

18:37.028 --> 18:38.508
[Dr. Welk]
Natalie.

18:38.552 --> 18:41.511
♪ ♪

18:41.555 --> 18:43.122
Natalie.

18:43.165 --> 18:45.341
Natalie!

18:45.385 --> 18:47.213
Natalie.

18:47.256 --> 18:49.476
What are you doing out here?

18:49.519 --> 18:50.433
[Natalie]
I don't know.

18:52.740 --> 18:54.133
[Dr. Welk]
Come on.

18:54.176 --> 18:56.439
Let's get you to the car.

18:56.483 --> 18:58.528
It's okay, come on.

19:06.188 --> 19:08.059
You're lucky I found you.

19:08.103 --> 19:09.583
You coulda wandered
into traffic,

19:09.626 --> 19:12.151
been seriously injured.

19:12.194 --> 19:14.240
What was the last thing
you remember?

19:14.283 --> 19:17.373
[Natalie]
Uh, I was at home.

19:17.417 --> 19:20.246
I went to bed.

19:20.289 --> 19:24.250
More memories from that night.

19:24.293 --> 19:26.339
Okay, but nothing new?

19:26.382 --> 19:28.471
[Natalie]
Nothing I can make sense of.

19:28.515 --> 19:29.994
Okay, I'll come in,
your Aunt Caroline needs

19:30.038 --> 19:31.474
- to know about this.
- No!

19:31.518 --> 19:33.868
[Dr. Welk]
Natalie, this is very serious.

19:33.911 --> 19:36.958
[Natalie]
I know, but she's already
been through so much,

19:37.001 --> 19:40.179
and with all this stuff
going on in the news, I just...

19:40.222 --> 19:43.094
I don't wanna give her
anything more to worry about.

19:43.138 --> 19:45.532
Okay, for now.

19:45.575 --> 19:46.750
But in lieu of that,

19:46.794 --> 19:48.404
you need to up your medication.

19:48.448 --> 19:49.710
Double the dose
you take at night

19:49.753 --> 19:53.540
until you get this
under control.

19:53.583 --> 19:58.197
Here's a refill
so you don't run out.

19:58.240 --> 19:59.633
Call me tomorrow morning,

19:59.676 --> 20:01.635
we'll set an earlier
appointment.

20:01.678 --> 20:02.810
[Natalie]
Thank you.

20:07.162 --> 20:09.556
[suspenseful music]

20:09.599 --> 20:13.255
♪ ♪

20:13.299 --> 20:15.736
Where the hell did I go?

20:15.779 --> 20:29.010
♪ ♪

20:29.053 --> 20:30.968
[Caroline]
You're up early.

20:31.012 --> 20:32.927
Uh, I wanted
to get to school on time

20:32.970 --> 20:35.756
to drop off my make-up work.

20:39.586 --> 20:42.763
Natalie, look.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.591
You were right,
those were your letters.

20:44.634 --> 20:47.463
I had no right to destroy them.

20:47.507 --> 20:50.292
I'm sorry.

20:50.336 --> 20:52.251
You had already been through
so much

20:52.294 --> 20:54.862
with your dad, and the cancer,

20:54.905 --> 20:56.777
and I just didn't want you
to suffer

20:56.820 --> 20:59.475
any more than you already had.

21:02.565 --> 21:05.046
Did you sleep okay?

21:05.089 --> 21:07.309
Great, thanks.

21:07.353 --> 21:09.616
- Nightmares?
- Nope.

21:09.659 --> 21:13.576
- Slept through the night.
- Good.

21:13.620 --> 21:16.318
Maybe the medication's
finally starting to work.

21:16.362 --> 21:19.930
I think so.

21:19.974 --> 21:21.758
Okay, I've gotta grab this,
all right?

21:21.802 --> 21:23.891
But I will see you
for dinner tonight, okay?

21:23.934 --> 21:25.284
I'll make you something special.

21:25.327 --> 21:26.546
[cell phone ringing]

21:26.589 --> 21:28.548
Okay.

21:28.591 --> 21:30.854
Yes, today's the day
of the offer, I'm on my way.

21:30.898 --> 21:32.639
I'll be there
in about 20 minutes.

21:32.682 --> 21:35.076
[unsettling music]

21:35.119 --> 21:45.172
♪ ♪

21:45.173 --> 21:57.054
♪ ♪

21:57.098 --> 21:59.448
[eerie music]

21:59.492 --> 22:04.670
♪ ♪

22:04.671 --> 22:09.502
♪ ♪

22:33.917 --> 22:36.311
[cell phone ringing]

22:36.355 --> 22:44.493
♪ ♪

22:44.537 --> 22:47.322
- Hello?
- Hey, just checking on you.

22:47.366 --> 22:48.802
You walking to school or what?

22:48.845 --> 22:51.413
Oh, sorry, I completely spaced.

22:51.457 --> 22:53.241
I'll meet you there.

22:53.284 --> 23:03.337
♪ ♪

23:03.338 --> 23:09.126
♪ ♪

23:16.003 --> 23:18.440
[principal]
Natalie.

23:18.484 --> 23:20.181
[Natalie]
Yes?

23:20.224 --> 23:22.966
[principal]
I need to see you in my office.

23:28.058 --> 23:30.321
Please, sit down.

23:37.546 --> 23:40.375
This is Captain Lawrence.

23:40.419 --> 23:42.986
[Captain Lawrence]
Hi Natalie, nice to meet you.

23:43.030 --> 23:45.293
Is this about the other day?

23:45.336 --> 23:48.862
I already did suspension,
and I'm still doing detention.

23:48.905 --> 23:50.994
We know.

23:51.038 --> 23:54.694
The captain just wants
to ask you some questions.

23:54.737 --> 23:57.479
Where were you last night?

23:57.523 --> 23:59.655
I was at home.

23:59.699 --> 24:02.441
All night?

24:02.484 --> 24:03.572
Yes.

24:03.616 --> 24:07.054
Why?

24:07.097 --> 24:11.101
Kent Shelton was attacked
last night.

24:11.145 --> 24:14.409
- Murdered.
- What?

24:14.453 --> 24:16.672
A hiker came across his body
this morning

24:16.716 --> 24:19.806
out by Pike's Trail.

24:19.849 --> 24:23.549
Oh my god.

24:23.592 --> 24:25.376
Is there anyone
that can corroborate

24:25.420 --> 24:27.857
your whereabouts last night?

24:27.901 --> 24:30.686
Wait, am I a suspect?

24:30.730 --> 24:33.341
We're just asking questions.

24:33.384 --> 24:35.778
[dramatic music]

24:35.822 --> 24:39.652
I was with my aunt.

24:39.695 --> 24:41.088
Do you know of anyone else

24:41.131 --> 24:43.482
who might've had a dispute
with Kent?

24:43.525 --> 24:46.267
♪ ♪

24:46.310 --> 24:48.487
Not exactly, I mean,

24:48.530 --> 24:51.315
there's a lot of people
that didn't like him.

24:51.359 --> 24:53.579
Like who?

24:53.622 --> 24:55.319
I don't know, really.

24:55.363 --> 24:57.626
I mean, I didn't hang out
with him or anything.

24:57.670 --> 25:00.020
♪ ♪

25:00.063 --> 25:01.848
[Captain Lawrence]
Thank you for your time.

25:01.891 --> 25:03.980
We'll be in touch
if we have any more questions.

25:04.024 --> 25:15.078
♪ ♪

25:23.826 --> 25:27.787
- Dr. Welk, how are you?
- Fine, hi.

25:27.830 --> 25:30.093
If you're looking for Natalie,
I think she's still at school.

25:30.137 --> 25:33.793
[Dr. Welk]
No, actually I'm here
to see you.

25:33.836 --> 25:36.404
Oh, uh, let's go inside then.

25:36.447 --> 25:37.797
- Okay.
- Okay.

25:37.840 --> 25:39.799
Sleepwalking last night?

25:39.842 --> 25:42.279
- How do you know?
- I found her

25:42.323 --> 25:44.586
walking down the street
over near the old foundry.

25:44.630 --> 25:47.763
Clothes filthy, feet muddy
with no recollection

25:47.807 --> 25:51.811
of where she'd been
or what she might have done.

25:51.854 --> 25:54.596
Well, she told me that
she slept through the night.

25:54.640 --> 25:55.815
I thought it was important
that you know,

25:55.858 --> 25:57.817
especially after what happened

25:57.860 --> 25:59.949
to that poor young man
they found this morning.

25:59.993 --> 26:02.299
You don't actually think
that Natalie had anything

26:02.343 --> 26:04.258
- to do with that?
- I have an obligation

26:04.301 --> 26:06.434
to inform authorities
if I think a patient

26:06.477 --> 26:09.350
is a danger to themselves
or others.

26:09.393 --> 26:10.786
Natalie's not a danger
to anyone,

26:10.830 --> 26:12.571
and you and I both know that.

26:12.614 --> 26:14.573
Yes, and we also both know
that she suffered

26:14.616 --> 26:16.226
a significant trauma as a child.

26:16.270 --> 26:18.272
Recent stressor events
that could draw that

26:18.315 --> 26:20.535
right back to the surface.

26:20.579 --> 26:23.233
Events like her mother's
impending execution.

26:23.277 --> 26:25.409
[solemn music]

26:25.453 --> 26:28.064
We know that she lied
about sleepwalking.

26:28.108 --> 26:30.850
Is it possible

26:30.893 --> 26:33.548
that she lied to you
about other things?

26:33.592 --> 26:46.082
♪ ♪

26:46.126 --> 26:48.563
[dramatic music]

26:48.607 --> 26:52.045
♪ ♪

26:52.088 --> 26:54.656
[Natalie]
I have no idea how I got there,

26:54.700 --> 26:57.616
or where I'd been.

26:57.659 --> 27:00.531
My psychiatrist,
Dr. Welk, found me.

27:00.575 --> 27:05.014
And this morning,
when I heard about Kent,

27:05.058 --> 27:09.236
I began to think,
"What if it was me?

27:09.279 --> 27:11.151
What if I did it?"

27:11.194 --> 27:13.849
Oh, Natalie, I'm so sorry.

27:13.893 --> 27:16.330
[banging]

27:18.027 --> 27:19.855
[Natalie]
I just can't remember.

27:19.899 --> 27:22.466
The medication's not helping.

27:22.510 --> 27:25.208
This Dr. Welk,
can you trust him?

27:25.252 --> 27:28.995
- Trust him?
- With your confidence.

27:29.038 --> 27:31.650
I think so, why?

27:31.693 --> 27:33.652
I wouldn't, don't say anything.

27:33.695 --> 27:36.393
Not to anyone,
not even Aunt Caroline.

27:36.437 --> 27:38.744
Do you understand me?

27:38.787 --> 27:41.529
Now, listen,
did you find anything?

27:41.572 --> 27:44.793
- Any evidence?
- Evidence?

27:44.837 --> 27:47.796
You know, like blood or skin
under your fingernails?

27:47.840 --> 27:50.799
[unsettling music]

27:50.843 --> 27:52.888
Whatever you wore last night,
just get rid of it.

27:52.932 --> 27:55.282
Bury it, burn it,
just destroy it

27:55.325 --> 27:57.588
so that nobody can ever find it.

27:57.632 --> 28:00.896
- Why?
- Because once people think

28:00.940 --> 28:02.550
that you're something,

28:02.593 --> 28:05.205
that's all
they're ever gonna see.

28:05.248 --> 28:06.859
Believe me, I know.

28:06.902 --> 28:09.296
I just wish I could remember

28:09.339 --> 28:12.299
last night
and when I was a child.

28:12.342 --> 28:15.998
I know, but trust me,
it's better that you don't.

28:16.042 --> 28:20.829
There are things that
I've never wanted you to know.

28:20.873 --> 28:24.441
What things,
what are you talking about?

28:24.485 --> 28:26.487
Just... it doesn't matter.

28:26.530 --> 28:29.185
Just do as I say.

28:29.229 --> 28:32.145
Keep taking your meds,
they'll help.

28:32.188 --> 28:36.758
And know that everything I did
was to protect you.

28:36.802 --> 28:38.760
Protect me?

28:38.804 --> 28:40.675
From what?

28:40.719 --> 28:43.069
[intense music]

28:43.112 --> 28:45.636
♪ ♪

28:48.814 --> 28:52.121
♪ ♪

28:58.824 --> 29:00.782
[Caroline]
Natalie, is everything okay?

29:00.826 --> 29:02.610
[Natalie]
Yeah, why?

29:02.653 --> 29:04.481
[Caroline]
Dr. Welk came by this afternoon.

29:04.525 --> 29:07.571
He said he found you
last night sleepwalking.

29:07.615 --> 29:09.922
Why did you lie to me?

29:09.965 --> 29:12.272
[Natalie]
'Cause I didn't wanna feel
like a freak.

29:12.315 --> 29:14.491
- For one day, at least.
- You're not a freak,

29:14.535 --> 29:16.755
and there's nothing
that you can't tell me.

29:16.798 --> 29:17.930
Do you understand?

29:17.973 --> 29:21.803
Look me in my eyes.

29:21.847 --> 29:24.763
Is there anything else
you haven't told me?

29:26.503 --> 29:29.680
[doorbell ringing]

29:29.724 --> 29:31.073
Stay here.

29:38.037 --> 29:39.255
♪ ♪

29:39.299 --> 29:41.083
Good evening, officers.

29:41.127 --> 29:42.824
Something wrong?

29:42.868 --> 29:45.435
[Captain Lawrence]
Actually, yes.

29:45.479 --> 29:48.438
We spoke to Dr. Welk
this afternoon.

29:48.482 --> 29:51.441
We have reason to believe
that Natalie misled us today.

29:51.485 --> 29:53.835
Misled you, about what?

29:53.879 --> 29:57.491
[Captain Lawrence]
About her whereabouts
last night.

29:57.534 --> 29:59.667
We have a search warrant.

29:59.710 --> 30:01.538
We'd like to see the clothes
Natalie was wearing

30:01.582 --> 30:04.498
- when she went to bed.
- Okay.

30:04.541 --> 30:06.892
[dramatic music]

30:06.935 --> 30:10.591
♪ ♪

30:10.634 --> 30:13.594
- They've been washed?
- It was laundry day.

30:13.637 --> 30:16.162
♪ ♪

30:16.205 --> 30:18.729
- Would you like a bag?
- Don't bother.

30:18.773 --> 30:20.340
We brought our own.

30:20.383 --> 30:28.391
♪ ♪

30:28.435 --> 30:32.395
I'm curious why Natalie didn't
mention sleepwalking last night.

30:32.439 --> 30:35.703
- She said she was home asleep.
- Oh, is that what she said

30:35.746 --> 30:39.707
when you were questioning her
without a lawyer present?

30:39.750 --> 30:43.015
[Captain Lawrence]
I'm just wondering
why she would lie.

30:43.058 --> 30:46.061
[Caroline]
Look, Natalie's not feeling
very socially welcome

30:46.105 --> 30:47.758
right now with her mom
in the news.

30:47.802 --> 30:49.412
Letting the world know
about her sleepwalking

30:49.456 --> 30:52.981
would hardly help that.

30:53.025 --> 30:54.635
Have a nice night.

30:54.678 --> 30:58.378
♪ ♪

30:59.901 --> 31:01.816
You don't do my laundry anymore.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.514
- You haven't for years.
- I had a load of laundry to do,

31:04.558 --> 31:05.994
so I just grabbed
some of your stuff.

31:06.038 --> 31:10.172
[Natalie]
What was on it? Tell me!

31:10.216 --> 31:12.522
[Caroline]
Spots, small ones.

31:12.566 --> 31:14.960
- Blood?
- I don't know what they were.

31:15.003 --> 31:17.963
- Oh my god.
- Listen.

31:18.006 --> 31:20.487
Whatever's going on right now
has nothing to do with you,

31:20.530 --> 31:22.924
all right, and if the school
or the police want to ask you

31:22.968 --> 31:25.361
any more questions,
you don't talk to them.

31:25.405 --> 31:28.190
- You have them talk to me.
- Because you think I did it!

31:28.234 --> 31:30.932
No, because it's my job
to protect you.

31:30.976 --> 31:34.283
That's just what Annie said,
that she was protecting me.

31:34.327 --> 31:37.504
[Caroline]
No, Natalie, she is a liar.

31:37.547 --> 31:40.724
She is only gonna tell you
what she wants you to hear

31:40.768 --> 31:42.944
and what makes her look good.

31:42.988 --> 31:48.036
♪ ♪

31:48.080 --> 31:51.126
[Dr. Welk]
Do the breathing exercises
three time a day.

31:51.170 --> 31:54.564
And remember, focus on
what you can control, Josh.

31:54.608 --> 31:56.175
Okay, see you next week.

31:56.218 --> 31:57.828
[Natalie]
You talked to the cops?

31:57.872 --> 32:00.309
Natalie,
your appointment is on...

32:00.353 --> 32:01.963
You told them
I was sleepwalking?

32:02.007 --> 32:05.097
- You need to calm down.
- Why would you do that?

32:05.140 --> 32:07.621
[Dr. Welk]
Look, I have an obligation
as a doctor...

32:07.664 --> 32:10.015
[Natalie]
Yeah, to help your patients!

32:10.058 --> 32:12.452
To inform the authorities
if I perceive a patient

32:12.495 --> 32:15.629
is a possible threat
to themselves or others.

32:15.672 --> 32:19.241
So, you think I'm a threat?

32:19.285 --> 32:21.765
To who, Kent?

32:21.809 --> 32:24.290
I think that you've been under
a great deal of stress lately.

32:24.333 --> 32:27.989
That coupled with your past
trauma could be triggering.

32:28.033 --> 32:30.818
So, you think I killed him?

32:30.861 --> 32:33.212
Look, let me ask you.

32:33.255 --> 32:34.996
Do you remember
what happened that night?

32:35.040 --> 32:36.911
Do you remember where you were?

32:36.955 --> 32:39.000
[eerie music]

32:39.044 --> 32:41.089
♪ ♪

32:41.133 --> 32:42.264
I have a patient coming.

32:42.308 --> 32:44.658
I think it's best

32:44.701 --> 32:46.268
if you leave.

32:46.312 --> 32:53.710
♪ ♪

32:53.754 --> 32:56.148
[cell phone ringing]

32:57.714 --> 32:59.978
- Yeah?
- Natalie.

33:00.021 --> 33:01.892
I thought of someone who might
be able to help you remember,

33:01.936 --> 33:03.242
someone who was there
that night.

33:03.285 --> 33:05.940
- Who is it?
- Captain John Matthews.

33:05.984 --> 33:07.289
I'm tied up at work right now,

33:07.333 --> 33:08.812
but maybe we can
go see him tomorrow.

33:08.856 --> 33:10.727
[Natalie]
No, I have to do it myself.

33:10.771 --> 33:13.121
[suspenseful music]

33:13.165 --> 33:15.863
♪ ♪

33:15.906 --> 33:18.300
[soft music]

33:18.344 --> 33:20.999
♪ ♪

33:21.042 --> 33:22.435
[Captain Matthews]
Don't even think about it.

33:22.478 --> 33:24.698
I can smell a fake ID
a mile away.

33:24.741 --> 33:27.962
[Natalie]
Um, I'm not here for a drink.

33:28.006 --> 33:30.486
Are you Captain Matthews?

33:30.530 --> 33:32.140
Who's asking?

33:32.184 --> 33:34.621
[Natalie]
I'm Natalie Weaver.

33:34.664 --> 33:38.364
Natalie Weaver.

33:38.407 --> 33:40.844
You're all grown up.

33:40.888 --> 33:42.194
[Natalie]
You remember me?

33:42.237 --> 33:43.543
'Course I remember you.

33:43.586 --> 33:46.285
[mellow music]

33:46.328 --> 33:49.462
You don't forget
a night like that.

33:49.505 --> 33:51.725
Then why can't I remember it?

33:51.768 --> 33:57.861
♪ ♪

33:57.905 --> 34:02.431
Things are happening now
and I need to know,

34:02.475 --> 34:05.217
are you sure my mom did it?

34:05.260 --> 34:07.262
Why would you even say
something like that?

34:07.306 --> 34:09.612
Your testimony was solid.

34:09.656 --> 34:12.789
- You convinced the jury.
- That's just it.

34:12.833 --> 34:15.966
I can barely remember
anything about that night.

34:16.010 --> 34:18.752
All right, look,
your memory might be foggy now,

34:18.795 --> 34:22.016
but back then, you were clear.

34:22.060 --> 34:24.149
And know this,

34:24.192 --> 34:27.195
Annie Weaver is bad news.

34:27.239 --> 34:29.328
Always has been.

34:29.371 --> 34:32.244
Whenever there was trouble,
Annie was never too far behind,

34:32.286 --> 34:35.116
and that night...

34:35.159 --> 34:36.944
Look,
whatever she's telling you,

34:36.987 --> 34:41.295
do not believe it.

34:41.340 --> 34:44.386
You sound like my Aunt Caroline.

34:44.429 --> 34:46.127
She sounds like a smart woman.

34:46.170 --> 34:48.998
You should listen to her.

34:49.043 --> 34:51.610
- Thank you.
- All right, any time.

34:51.654 --> 34:54.135
[indistinct chatter]

34:54.179 --> 34:56.616
[unsettling music]

34:56.659 --> 35:00.272
♪ ♪

35:00.315 --> 35:04.058
So, Natalie,
did you draw all of these?

35:04.102 --> 35:08.715
♪ ♪

35:08.758 --> 35:11.848
Can you explain this one to me?

35:11.892 --> 35:16.157
Is this a picture of the couple
who rented the room upstairs?

35:16.201 --> 35:18.072
Is this the Millers?

35:18.116 --> 35:26.646
♪ ♪

35:26.689 --> 35:29.779
I was mad.

35:29.823 --> 35:32.434
Why were you mad?

35:32.478 --> 35:36.177
Because...

35:36.221 --> 35:37.787
they were going away.

35:37.831 --> 35:40.225
♪ ♪

35:40.268 --> 35:42.140
They acted like,

35:42.183 --> 35:45.143
like my family,

35:45.186 --> 35:47.841
and then they were leaving.

35:47.884 --> 35:49.843
Just like Dad.

35:49.886 --> 35:53.586
♪ ♪

35:53.629 --> 35:56.066
My mom told me to draw

35:56.110 --> 35:59.592
how I was feeling.

35:59.635 --> 36:01.550
They were going away.

36:01.594 --> 36:05.250
I wanted them to go away...

36:05.293 --> 36:08.340
forever.

36:08.383 --> 36:11.169
I never wanted
to see them again.

36:11.212 --> 36:13.214
♪ ♪

36:13.258 --> 36:14.998
They were dead to me.

36:15.042 --> 36:23.703
♪ ♪

36:27.228 --> 36:28.925
[bell jingling]

36:30.884 --> 36:32.668
[Natalie]
Sorry, I know I'm late.

36:32.712 --> 36:35.149
[Owen]
Yeah, I'm sorry too.

36:37.586 --> 36:40.676
- I gotta let you go, Nat.
- What? No.

36:40.720 --> 36:43.375
I was just... okay, like an hour.

36:43.418 --> 36:45.942
I'll stay late
or make it up tomorrow.

36:45.986 --> 36:48.771
The police came by asking
about you and that young man.

36:48.815 --> 36:50.382
Kent, was it?

36:50.425 --> 36:52.122
I mean, it's hard enough
keeping this place going

36:52.166 --> 36:54.081
without that kind
of negative attention.

36:54.124 --> 36:56.692
Please, Owen, I need this job.

36:56.736 --> 36:58.520
I'm saving for college
next year.

36:58.564 --> 37:00.479
I need this job too,

37:00.522 --> 37:03.133
but lately, we get more gawkers
than customers.

37:03.177 --> 37:04.657
So, that's it then?

37:04.700 --> 37:06.485
All because of a bunch of lies?

37:06.528 --> 37:08.269
Well, screw you, then!

37:08.313 --> 37:10.750
[dramatic music]

37:10.793 --> 37:16.190
♪ ♪

37:16.234 --> 37:19.106
[soft music]

37:19.149 --> 37:21.587
[beeping]

37:29.290 --> 37:30.465
What is that?

37:30.509 --> 37:32.380
It's a sensor for an alarm,

37:32.424 --> 37:34.904
so I'll know if you sneak out
in the middle of the night.

37:34.948 --> 37:38.734
- Great, now I'm a prisoner.
- It's just a precaution.

37:38.778 --> 37:40.954
[Natalie]
To prevent me from maybe
killing someone else.

37:40.997 --> 37:44.000
[Caroline]
Stop it, I don't believe that
and neither should you.

37:44.044 --> 37:46.176
Well, the whole town seems to.

37:46.220 --> 37:48.309
And before you hear it
from someone else,

37:48.353 --> 37:50.659
along with all the other rumors,

37:50.703 --> 37:54.097
- I got fired today.
- Fired, why?

37:54.141 --> 37:58.667
Because I'm bad for business
or something.

37:58.711 --> 38:01.496
- I'll go talk to him.
- Don't, please.

38:01.540 --> 38:03.281
I know you're just trying
to help,

38:03.324 --> 38:06.327
but the more distance
you keep from me,

38:06.371 --> 38:08.677
the better your life will be.

38:08.721 --> 38:11.201
[melancholy music]

38:11.245 --> 38:13.334
♪ ♪

38:13.378 --> 38:15.728
[eerie music]

38:15.771 --> 38:20.949
♪ ♪

38:20.950 --> 38:25.781
♪ ♪

38:48.413 --> 38:50.371
[alarm blaring]

38:50.415 --> 38:52.068
[Caroline]
Natalie?

38:58.640 --> 39:00.729
Natalie?

39:00.773 --> 39:02.818
Natalie!

39:05.038 --> 39:07.257
[thudding]

39:07.301 --> 39:10.609
[suspenseful music]

39:10.652 --> 39:12.524
Hello?

39:12.567 --> 39:14.134
We're closed.

39:14.177 --> 39:18.399
♪ ♪

39:18.443 --> 39:20.227
Is somebody there?

39:20.270 --> 39:27.190
♪ ♪

39:27.234 --> 39:28.844
Hello?

39:28.888 --> 39:36.809
♪ ♪

39:36.852 --> 39:39.812
Who's in here?

39:39.855 --> 39:42.423
You better come out
or I'm gonna call the police.

39:42.467 --> 39:52.476
♪ ♪

39:52.477 --> 40:01.442
♪ ♪

40:01.486 --> 40:03.836
[engine whirring]

40:06.578 --> 40:08.971
[somber music]

40:09.015 --> 40:23.421
♪ ♪

40:23.464 --> 40:25.074
[Caroline]
Natalie?

40:25.118 --> 40:26.946
Are you awake?

40:26.989 --> 40:29.514
♪ ♪

40:29.557 --> 40:31.516
- What am I doing here?
- I don't know, baby.

40:31.559 --> 40:32.647
Let's get you home.

40:32.691 --> 40:34.127
Okay? Come on.

40:34.170 --> 40:37.826
♪ ♪

40:37.870 --> 40:39.393
[coroner]
Let's confirm
with Officer Johnson

40:39.437 --> 40:40.960
that he dusted the fingerprints
on the rear door.

40:41.003 --> 40:43.484
- Okay?
- Yeah, okay.

40:43.528 --> 40:46.661
[coroner]
Captain Lawrence,
victim's name is Owen Moore.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.271
He's the store owner.

40:48.315 --> 40:50.099
From what we can tell,
someone gained access

40:50.143 --> 40:51.536
from the rear door.

40:51.579 --> 40:53.015
Defensive wounds
on his hands indicate

40:53.059 --> 40:56.236
he tried to defend himself.

40:56.279 --> 40:58.281
The initial attack
happened here.

40:58.325 --> 41:01.328
Then the victim tried
to crawl free.

41:01.371 --> 41:02.895
[Captain Lawrence]
Hm.

41:02.938 --> 41:04.766
[eerie music]

41:04.810 --> 41:06.986
♪ ♪

41:07.029 --> 41:09.945
[coroner]
He was killed
with a meat cleaver.

41:09.989 --> 41:12.208
- Just like the Shelton kid.
- Mm-hm.

41:12.252 --> 41:15.995
[Captain Lawrence]
Same weapon used, same MO.

41:16.038 --> 41:17.953
[coroner]
Several customers said
he had a heated conversation

41:17.997 --> 41:20.913
with an employee yesterday
before he fired her.

41:20.956 --> 41:24.525
- Her?
- Natalie Weaver works here,

41:24.569 --> 41:27.963
or did until yesterday.

41:28.007 --> 41:29.487
♪ ♪

41:29.530 --> 41:30.444
[sighing]

41:35.188 --> 41:37.538
[doorbell ringing]

41:42.761 --> 41:44.502
[dark music]

41:44.545 --> 41:47.026
[Captain Lawrence]
Good morning. Is Natalie here?

41:47.069 --> 41:49.071
[Caroline]
She's not,
she went to school early

41:49.115 --> 41:51.378
to catch up on some homework.

41:51.421 --> 41:54.294
- May we come in?
- Sure.

41:54.337 --> 42:00.735
♪ ♪

42:00.779 --> 42:03.564
[Captain Lawrence]
Do you know Natalie's
whereabouts last night?

42:03.608 --> 42:04.913
She was home.

42:04.957 --> 42:06.480
She was with me, sleeping

42:06.524 --> 42:08.526
until she got up for school
this morning.

42:08.569 --> 42:11.093
[Captain Lawrence]
No chance she may have
woken during the night,

42:11.137 --> 42:13.443
slipped out?

42:13.487 --> 42:15.358
What's this about, Captain?

42:15.402 --> 42:17.796
[Captain Lawrence]
Owen Moore was murdered
last night,

42:17.839 --> 42:19.841
killed in his shop.

42:19.885 --> 42:23.758
Oh, my God, that's awful.

42:23.802 --> 42:25.586
[Captain Lawrence]
Natalie worked there,
didn't she?

42:25.630 --> 42:27.849
- She did.
- We have reports

42:27.893 --> 42:30.417
from several customers
that she engaged

42:30.460 --> 42:33.638
in a heated argument with Owen
just yesterday,

42:33.681 --> 42:36.205
similar to her outburst
with Kent Shelton

42:36.249 --> 42:38.556
before he was murdered.

42:38.599 --> 42:40.166
This is insane.

42:40.209 --> 42:41.776
I know it may not look like it,

42:41.820 --> 42:43.517
but I'm trying to help.

42:43.561 --> 42:44.823
You're right.

42:44.866 --> 42:46.955
It doesn't look like it.

42:46.999 --> 42:48.914
After you came by
the other night,

42:48.957 --> 42:52.657
I installed these alarms
on all the doors just in case.

42:52.700 --> 42:55.094
If Natalie slipped out,
I'd know.

42:55.137 --> 42:57.662
And she was here all night.

42:57.705 --> 42:59.315
Now...

42:59.359 --> 43:00.926
♪ ♪

43:00.969 --> 43:02.710
If you would like to talk
to Natalie again,

43:02.754 --> 43:05.974
I'll arrange it, this time
with an attorney present.

43:06.018 --> 43:09.674
[Captain Lawrence]
All right, if that's the way
you want it.

43:09.717 --> 43:11.023
We'll talk soon.

43:11.066 --> 43:13.025
Good day.

43:13.068 --> 43:21.642
♪ ♪

43:21.686 --> 43:23.688
Natalie?

43:23.731 --> 43:33.784
♪ ♪

43:33.785 --> 43:41.488
♪ ♪

43:41.531 --> 43:43.882
[indistinct chatter]

44:00.115 --> 44:02.465
[dramatic music]

44:02.509 --> 44:12.561
♪ ♪

44:12.562 --> 44:17.742
♪ ♪

44:17.785 --> 44:20.353
[gasping]

44:20.396 --> 44:30.449
♪ ♪

44:30.450 --> 44:38.327
♪ ♪

44:38.371 --> 44:41.069
[grunting]

44:41.113 --> 44:43.071
Geoff?

44:43.115 --> 44:45.508
Why are you following me?

44:45.552 --> 44:47.597
♪ ♪

44:47.641 --> 44:49.643
[Geoff]
Uh, Natalie, don't.

44:49.687 --> 44:51.863
♪ ♪

44:51.906 --> 44:53.952
What the hell?

44:53.995 --> 44:55.562
Why do you have this?

44:55.605 --> 44:56.955
It's not what it looks like.

44:56.998 --> 44:58.434
Then what is it?

44:58.478 --> 45:00.349
It's for protection...

45:00.393 --> 45:02.003
♪ ♪

45:02.047 --> 45:04.745
...in case I ran
into the killer.

45:04.789 --> 45:06.355
Oh my god.

45:06.399 --> 45:07.835
It's you.

45:07.879 --> 45:08.923
What?

45:08.967 --> 45:10.751
You killed them.

45:10.795 --> 45:14.015
You've been following me
and setting me up.

45:14.059 --> 45:15.800
You hated Kent.

45:15.843 --> 45:18.063
You had just as much reason
to kill him as I did.

45:18.106 --> 45:19.020
No.

45:19.064 --> 45:21.022
And Owen.

45:21.066 --> 45:22.328
You were there that day.

45:22.371 --> 45:24.852
Natalie, you're talking crazy.

45:24.896 --> 45:26.549
No, you're crazy!

45:26.593 --> 45:27.986
You're doing all of this.

45:28.029 --> 45:30.771
I told you, it's for protection.

45:30.815 --> 45:32.773
- Now give it back.
- No.

45:32.817 --> 45:34.993
Stay away from me.

45:35.036 --> 45:36.995
Natalie.

45:37.038 --> 45:38.997
Stop!

45:39.040 --> 45:50.660
♪ ♪

45:54.839 --> 45:56.492
[Caroline]
Natalie, are you okay?

45:56.536 --> 45:58.581
I was trying to get home
and I ran into Geoff.

45:58.625 --> 46:00.496
He's doing this, all of it.

46:00.540 --> 46:02.150
Geoff? No, honey.

46:02.194 --> 46:03.717
[Natalie]
He was following me.

46:03.761 --> 46:07.416
And look what I found
in his backpack.

46:07.460 --> 46:10.028
He said it was for protection,
but it has to be him.

46:10.071 --> 46:11.333
Why else would he have it?

46:11.377 --> 46:13.945
Why else would he be
following me?

46:13.988 --> 46:16.121
Because I asked him to.

46:16.164 --> 46:18.776
You asked him to? Why?

46:18.819 --> 46:20.647
I needed someone to look
after you when I couldn't.

46:20.690 --> 46:22.475
Okay, I was worried.

46:22.518 --> 46:25.043
Honey, you've been
under a lot of stress lately,

46:25.086 --> 46:27.610
and Geoff was willing
to do that.

46:27.654 --> 46:30.875
He was willing to spy on me,
pretend to be my friend.

46:30.918 --> 46:33.312
- Natalie, stop.
- No, you stop!

46:33.355 --> 46:35.575
Stop lying to me!

46:35.618 --> 46:37.925
My whole life,
all of it has been a lie.

46:37.969 --> 46:40.058
Natalie, that is ridiculous.

46:40.101 --> 46:42.756
Why are you so sure
it's not Geoff?

46:42.800 --> 46:45.672
Because he agreed
to keep an eye on me?

46:45.715 --> 46:49.154
And how do you know
I'm innocent?

46:49.197 --> 46:52.461
I just know, okay?

46:52.505 --> 46:55.160
But you aren't really sure,
are you?

46:55.203 --> 46:56.857
[soft music]

46:56.901 --> 46:59.904
Neither am I.

46:59.947 --> 47:01.514
You should protect yourself.

47:01.557 --> 47:03.733
Lock your door.

47:03.777 --> 47:05.213
[Caroline]
Natalie, wait.

47:05.257 --> 47:07.781
Okay, where are you gonna go?

47:07.825 --> 47:10.305
Please just let me
take you home.

47:10.349 --> 47:14.005
♪ ♪

47:17.051 --> 47:19.401
[siren wailing]

47:20.925 --> 47:23.318
[tense music]

47:23.362 --> 47:28.540
♪ ♪

47:28.541 --> 47:33.372
♪ ♪

47:48.866 --> 47:50.911
Why aren't they here?

47:50.955 --> 47:52.782
♪ ♪

48:05.926 --> 48:09.538
[female reporter]
Natalie, did you kill
Kent Shelton?

48:09.582 --> 48:11.453
[male reporter]
Why did you not visit your
mother in prison earlier?

48:11.497 --> 48:12.498
[female reporter]
Do you know more
than you're saying

48:12.541 --> 48:13.760
about the murder of the Millers?

48:13.803 --> 48:15.457
- Channel Six...
- No comment.

48:15.501 --> 48:18.591
- Any comment, any comment?
- Natalie, Natalie!

48:18.634 --> 48:21.768
[shouting]

48:21.811 --> 48:23.988
[Caroline]
Go.

48:24.031 --> 48:26.425
[cell phone ringing]

48:28.514 --> 48:30.777
Yes?

48:30.820 --> 48:34.346
No! And if you print that,
I'm gonna take legal action.

48:34.389 --> 48:35.913
Natalie.

48:37.871 --> 48:40.352
Whatever you do,
you don't say a word to them.

48:40.395 --> 48:42.093
You lied to the police,

48:42.136 --> 48:43.964
told them I was here
when I wasn't.

48:44.008 --> 48:47.402
If they find out,
you'll be in so much trouble.

48:47.446 --> 48:48.969
I will deal with it.

48:49.013 --> 48:51.450
You have to stop protecting me
for your own sake!

48:51.493 --> 48:52.886
Well, I'm never
gonna stop doing that.

48:52.930 --> 48:54.496
You should.

48:54.540 --> 48:58.500
You're not my mother,
so stop acting like it.

48:58.544 --> 49:00.981
[somber music]

49:01.025 --> 49:02.243
♪ ♪

49:07.509 --> 49:09.381
[Captain Lawrence]
John?

49:12.297 --> 49:14.386
[Captain Matthews]
Maggie Lawrence.

49:15.953 --> 49:18.042
Been a while.

49:21.741 --> 49:23.699
[Officer Lawrence]
I need to ask you
a few questions.

49:23.743 --> 49:26.528
Yeah, figured as much.

49:26.572 --> 49:29.705
The, uh, Weaver murders?

49:33.883 --> 49:35.842
[Captain Lawrence]
You were the first one
on the scene.

49:35.885 --> 49:38.192
Ha, lucky me.

49:40.325 --> 49:44.198
[Captain Lawrence]
Natalie was there
that night, yes?

49:44.242 --> 49:47.723
Two people are dead.

49:47.767 --> 49:51.814
If you have any information
that would help us,

49:51.858 --> 49:55.209
anything that wasn't included

49:55.253 --> 49:58.299
in the official reports.

49:58.343 --> 50:02.695
Left more than a few things
out of the press report.

50:02.738 --> 50:06.525
Facts, details.

50:06.568 --> 50:09.919
Things like buttons
placed over the victims' eyes?

50:13.445 --> 50:15.838
This is from
last night's murder.

50:15.882 --> 50:18.363
[eerie music]

50:18.406 --> 50:23.150
And this, from two days ago.

50:23.194 --> 50:25.674
I've been going through
the files on the Weaver murders

50:25.718 --> 50:28.286
and there's something
I can't find.

50:28.329 --> 50:30.766
In her statement, Annie claimed

50:30.810 --> 50:34.727
that Natalie's drawings had
taken on a more hostile tone.

50:34.770 --> 50:36.729
♪ ♪

50:36.772 --> 50:40.472
But I can't find the drawings
anywhere in the files.

50:40.515 --> 50:42.387
And you won't find them.

50:42.430 --> 50:43.997
♪ ♪

50:44.041 --> 50:46.086
You saw them?

50:46.130 --> 50:57.837
♪ ♪

50:57.880 --> 51:00.274
[ripping]

51:00.318 --> 51:03.364
♪ ♪

51:03.408 --> 51:05.323
They don't exist anymore.

51:05.366 --> 51:07.281
My God, John.

51:07.325 --> 51:09.501
Why?

51:09.544 --> 51:13.200
'Cause Annie Weaver...

51:13.244 --> 51:15.072
she's trouble.

51:15.115 --> 51:17.117
And I was sick of it!

51:17.161 --> 51:19.119
I was done watching her
get away with it,

51:19.163 --> 51:21.426
so I did what was needed
to be done

51:21.469 --> 51:24.298
to protect innocent people!

51:24.342 --> 51:25.908
♪ ♪

51:25.952 --> 51:28.650
At least...

51:28.694 --> 51:30.826
I thought I did.

51:30.870 --> 51:32.872
♪ ♪

51:32.915 --> 51:35.004
I messed up, Mags.

51:35.048 --> 51:36.963
I messed up.

51:37.006 --> 51:42.664
♪ ♪

51:42.708 --> 51:44.362
[Captain Lawrence]
Yeah.

51:44.405 --> 51:46.277
You did.

51:46.320 --> 51:50.107
♪ ♪

51:50.150 --> 51:52.848
[lawyer]
So, with all
the obvious similarities

51:52.892 --> 51:55.851
to the original murders,

51:55.895 --> 51:58.506
there's no way they can
deny us a retrial.

51:58.550 --> 51:59.855
♪ ♪

51:59.899 --> 52:01.509
Yeah.

52:01.553 --> 52:02.815
I'm expecting
a stay of execution

52:02.858 --> 52:05.165
later this afternoon.

52:05.209 --> 52:06.993
God!

52:07.036 --> 52:08.516
[somber music]

52:08.560 --> 52:11.302
- And what about Natalie?
- I'd have to assume

52:11.345 --> 52:15.349
that she's a prime suspect
in their investigation.

52:15.393 --> 52:16.959
What?

52:17.003 --> 52:18.483
No.

52:18.526 --> 52:21.268
[lawyer]
Listen to me.

52:21.312 --> 52:23.140
This is good for us.

52:23.183 --> 52:25.838
A new trial means
a new chance at bail.

52:25.881 --> 52:27.535
No, but I want out of this cage,

52:27.579 --> 52:30.364
but not to put her in it.

52:30.408 --> 52:31.887
I will not betray her.

52:31.931 --> 52:33.541
She is a good girl.

52:33.585 --> 52:35.891
I understand.

52:35.935 --> 52:38.590
But let me make this clear
for you.

52:38.633 --> 52:40.722
This is going to save your life.

52:40.766 --> 52:43.421
Look, Annie, your daughter
is already a suspect

52:43.464 --> 52:45.379
in the new murders,
and there's nothing

52:45.423 --> 52:49.122
we can do to change that.

52:49.166 --> 52:51.385
Now you want to help her,

52:51.429 --> 52:54.997
you can do her more good
out there than in here.

52:55.041 --> 52:58.262
♪ ♪

52:58.305 --> 53:00.786
[Captain Lawrence]
Eight years ago,
this community was rocked

53:00.829 --> 53:03.876
by a vicious double homicide.

53:03.919 --> 53:05.660
The investigation
into those crimes

53:05.704 --> 53:08.663
pointed to a single
primary suspect

53:08.707 --> 53:11.362
who was later tried
and found guilty.

53:11.405 --> 53:14.321
But recent attacks
in our community

53:14.365 --> 53:16.236
have mirrored
the original crimes

53:16.280 --> 53:18.630
in ways that are undeniable
to dismiss

53:18.673 --> 53:20.284
and have caused us to re-examine

53:20.327 --> 53:22.242
the old investigation.

53:22.286 --> 53:24.157
Upon re-examining
the prior case,

53:24.201 --> 53:26.072
it was discovered that evidence

53:26.115 --> 53:29.293
potentially pointing
to other suspects

53:29.336 --> 53:32.905
was concealed,
was, in fact, destroyed.

53:32.948 --> 53:34.863
Due to this new information,

53:34.907 --> 53:37.431
Judge Oberman has overturned
Annie Weaver's conviction

53:37.475 --> 53:39.477
and has set her free
from prison,

53:39.520 --> 53:41.783
effective immediately.

53:41.827 --> 53:44.612
The investigation
will be reopened.

53:44.656 --> 53:46.223
We have several persons
of interest

53:46.266 --> 53:47.398
in the recent attacks

53:47.441 --> 53:49.226
and we will be pursuing
all leads.

53:49.269 --> 53:51.402
Due to the ongoing nature
of the investigation,

53:51.445 --> 53:53.186
there's little else
I can comment on.

53:53.230 --> 53:54.970
Thank you.

53:55.014 --> 53:58.060
[piano music]

53:58.104 --> 53:59.758
[Natalie]
We should tell them
about Geoff,

53:59.801 --> 54:01.716
what I found, the knife.

54:01.760 --> 54:03.414
No, honey,
then it's just gonna look

54:03.457 --> 54:05.677
like you're laying blame
on someone else.

54:05.720 --> 54:08.375
And besides, we have no proof
that he did anything anyway.

54:08.419 --> 54:10.334
[sighing]

54:10.377 --> 54:13.250
[tense music]

54:13.293 --> 54:15.252
I think you should
stay home today.

54:15.295 --> 54:18.080
And just sit here,
waiting for them to arrest me?

54:18.124 --> 54:20.909
No thanks.

54:20.953 --> 54:22.346
[Caroline]
Where are you going?

54:22.389 --> 54:24.304
Natalie!

54:24.348 --> 54:26.393
♪ ♪

54:26.437 --> 54:28.874
[buzzing, beeping]

54:28.917 --> 54:31.311
[soft music]

54:31.355 --> 54:34.314
♪ ♪

54:34.358 --> 54:36.838
[buzzing]

54:36.882 --> 54:51.810
♪ ♪

54:51.853 --> 54:53.638
- Annie, Annie!
- Over here!

54:53.681 --> 54:55.770
- Annie, Annie!
- Are you gonna file a lawsuit?

54:55.814 --> 54:56.771
- Annie, over here!
- How does it feel

54:56.815 --> 54:59.034
to be a free woman?

54:59.078 --> 55:00.340
[female reporter]
Mrs. Weaver! Mrs. Weaver,
are you gonna file

55:00.384 --> 55:03.038
a defamation suit?

55:03.082 --> 55:04.910
[male reporter]
Did you know about Natalie
from the beginning?

55:04.953 --> 55:06.215
[female reporter]
Why would you not tell the world
what you knew

55:06.259 --> 55:09.218
to spare your own life?

55:09.262 --> 55:11.438
Clearly, you're not a mother.

55:11.482 --> 55:12.657
[female reporter]
Annie, the public
wants to know,

55:12.700 --> 55:14.572
tell us more
about your sacrifice.

55:14.615 --> 55:16.356
All right, hey, thank you,
that's enough.

55:16.400 --> 55:17.618
I'll issue a statement later.

55:17.662 --> 55:19.925
- Okay? Thank you.
- Annie!

55:19.968 --> 55:21.709
[female reporter]
Annie, did you always know
about your daughter?

55:21.753 --> 55:23.668
[indistinct chatter]

55:25.104 --> 55:26.235
[lawyer]
Oh.

55:26.279 --> 55:28.716
Congratulations.

55:28.760 --> 55:30.370
A free woman.

55:30.414 --> 55:31.893
How does it feel?

55:31.937 --> 55:34.200
[Annie]
Long overdue.

55:34.243 --> 55:36.811
[lawyer]
I've been fielding offers
for interviews all day.

55:36.855 --> 55:39.292
We're gonna make this
financially worthwhile.

55:39.336 --> 55:41.250
In the meantime,
the police have set you up

55:41.294 --> 55:44.297
in a local motel,
all expenses paid.

55:44.341 --> 55:46.038
- How kind of them.
- I'll tell you, though,

55:46.081 --> 55:48.214
it's not the Ritz,
but at least your room

55:48.257 --> 55:51.391
is registered under an alias
so the press won't find you.

55:51.435 --> 55:53.611
[Annie]
Fine.

55:53.654 --> 55:56.178
But we have to make
one stop first.

55:56.222 --> 55:57.832
[lawyer]
Okay.

56:00.008 --> 56:02.402
[eerie mus]

56:02.446 --> 56:07.580
♪ ♪

56:07.581 --> 56:12.412
♪ ♪

57:01.461 --> 57:04.812
[Annie]
Oh, don't cry, baby,
everything is gonna be okay.

57:04.856 --> 57:06.379
♪ ♪

57:06.423 --> 57:09.643
Just take my hand.

57:09.687 --> 57:11.471
Come on.

57:11.515 --> 57:13.691
Mommy is gonna fix everything.

57:13.734 --> 57:16.476
That's my good girl.

57:16.520 --> 57:19.827
♪ ♪

57:19.871 --> 57:21.133
It's okay.

57:21.176 --> 57:22.743
♪ ♪

57:22.787 --> 57:23.962
Come on.

57:24.005 --> 57:27.356
Now, give Mommy the cleaver.

57:27.400 --> 57:41.588
♪ ♪

57:41.632 --> 57:44.504
Oh my god.

57:44.548 --> 57:47.246
It was me.

57:47.289 --> 57:49.248
I did it.

57:49.291 --> 57:50.336
♪ ♪

57:55.472 --> 57:56.908
Annie.

57:56.951 --> 57:59.824
Nice to see you, too, Caroline.

57:59.867 --> 58:01.521
I came to see my daughter.

58:01.565 --> 58:04.132
Natalie's not here.

58:06.265 --> 58:09.137
Nice place you got here.

58:09.181 --> 58:10.530
Certainly better than
where I've spent

58:10.574 --> 58:12.489
the last eight years.

58:12.532 --> 58:15.796
[Caroline]
Well, you did that
to yourself.

58:15.840 --> 58:17.929
We both know that's not true.

58:17.972 --> 58:20.584
The police did it
and you helped.

58:20.627 --> 58:22.629
You never did like me,

58:22.673 --> 58:25.589
from the day I started
dating your brother.

58:25.632 --> 58:27.286
Okay, what do you want?

58:27.329 --> 58:29.549
The keys to my mom's old house.

58:29.593 --> 58:31.333
I'm assuming
you still have them.

58:31.377 --> 58:33.118
Of course I do.

58:33.161 --> 58:34.467
It's really hard to sell a house

58:34.511 --> 58:37.165
where a double homicide
took place.

58:37.209 --> 58:39.516
The keys.

58:51.615 --> 58:54.226
[dark music]

58:54.269 --> 58:57.925
♪ ♪

58:57.969 --> 58:59.144
Once I get things in order,

58:59.187 --> 59:01.189
Natalie can come
move in with me.

59:01.233 --> 59:04.366
We have a lot
of catching up to do.

59:04.410 --> 59:07.544
- That is, until we move.
- Move?

59:07.587 --> 59:09.197
Well, you can't expect us
to stay here,

59:09.241 --> 59:10.982
not after everything
that's happened.

59:11.025 --> 59:13.767
We need a fresh start.

59:13.811 --> 59:16.509
Well, you can't take her.

59:16.553 --> 59:18.903
Oh, Caroline.

59:18.946 --> 59:22.080
After all these years
of playing a mother,

59:22.123 --> 59:24.996
you actually forgot
that you're not one.

59:25.039 --> 59:27.607
I have raised her.

59:27.651 --> 59:30.044
I have cared for her
like she is my own.

59:30.088 --> 59:33.004
Well, then you should want
what's best for her.

59:33.047 --> 59:37.356
Natalie needs to be somewhere
where people won't avoid her,

59:37.399 --> 59:39.488
won't be afraid of her.

59:39.532 --> 59:41.621
Afraid of her?

59:41.665 --> 59:45.407
Don't play dumb, Caroline.

59:45.451 --> 59:48.497
Even if she's proved innocent,

59:48.541 --> 59:51.413
it would take years
for people not to look at her

59:51.457 --> 59:54.199
with fear and suspicion.

59:54.242 --> 59:57.681
Trust me, I know.

59:57.724 --> 01:00:00.292
[soft music]

01:00:00.335 --> 01:00:03.643
Here's where I'm staying.

01:00:03.687 --> 01:00:06.907
Tell Natalie
to come see her mother.

01:00:06.951 --> 01:00:10.998
Or maybe I'll just text her.

01:00:11.042 --> 01:00:13.522
[suspenseful music]

01:00:13.566 --> 01:00:18.744
♪ ♪

01:00:18.745 --> 01:00:23.576
♪ ♪

01:00:48.340 --> 01:00:50.690
Like I said...

01:00:50.734 --> 01:00:52.649
it's not The Ritz.

01:00:52.692 --> 01:00:56.957
But you'll have
plenty of privacy.

01:00:57.001 --> 01:01:00.961
Compared to where I've been,
I'll take it.

01:01:01.005 --> 01:01:02.571
[lawyer]
I'll call you tomorrow.

01:01:02.615 --> 01:01:05.139
We'll get started on
the unlawful imprisonment suit.

01:01:05.183 --> 01:01:08.186
Get some rest.

01:01:08.229 --> 01:01:10.667
[soft music]

01:01:10.710 --> 01:01:16.890
♪ ♪

01:01:16.934 --> 01:01:18.631
[Caroline]
Natalie!

01:01:18.675 --> 01:01:20.198
[rapid footsteps]

01:01:20.241 --> 01:01:21.852
Natalie?

01:01:23.331 --> 01:01:25.507
Natalie, what's going on?

01:01:25.551 --> 01:01:26.552
What's wrong?

01:01:26.595 --> 01:01:27.901
Just stay away from me.

01:01:27.945 --> 01:01:30.208
Stay awa... why would I do that?

01:01:30.251 --> 01:01:31.862
It's safer that way.

01:01:31.905 --> 01:01:34.255
Safer? Honey, what are you
talking about?

01:01:36.301 --> 01:01:40.131
I saw it, what happened.

01:01:40.174 --> 01:01:41.828
I was at my old house.

01:01:41.872 --> 01:01:44.265
Something kept
drawing me back there.

01:01:44.309 --> 01:01:48.313
I went in
and finally remembered.

01:01:48.356 --> 01:01:51.359
No thanks to these!

01:01:51.403 --> 01:01:53.448
What did you see?

01:01:53.492 --> 01:01:56.713
I was holding the cleaver.

01:01:56.756 --> 01:01:58.976
It was all bloody.

01:01:59.019 --> 01:02:00.760
I killed them!

01:02:00.804 --> 01:02:02.893
No. That's not true.

01:02:02.936 --> 01:02:04.111
It is!

01:02:04.155 --> 01:02:06.331
I saw it, it was me!

01:02:06.374 --> 01:02:10.639
Look, Natalie, I don't know
what you saw or why,

01:02:10.683 --> 01:02:12.772
but that's not
the Natalie I know!

01:02:12.816 --> 01:02:15.296
Well, then maybe
you don't know then.

01:02:15.340 --> 01:02:19.823
I don't even know myself,
because that's who I am.

01:02:19.866 --> 01:02:21.912
Stop protecting me.

01:02:21.955 --> 01:02:23.783
I'm not worth it.

01:02:23.827 --> 01:02:25.785
[melancholy music]

01:02:25.829 --> 01:02:29.049
♪ ♪

01:02:29.093 --> 01:02:31.138
[eerie music]

01:02:31.182 --> 01:02:41.234
♪ ♪

01:02:41.235 --> 01:02:48.590
♪ ♪

01:02:48.634 --> 01:02:50.114
I got you.

01:02:50.157 --> 01:02:52.333
♪ ♪

01:02:54.292 --> 01:02:56.163
[knocking]

01:02:59.645 --> 01:03:00.777
Natalie!

01:03:00.820 --> 01:03:02.735
You got my text!

01:03:02.779 --> 01:03:05.869
Oh god!

01:03:05.912 --> 01:03:08.872
You have no idea
how much I've missed you.

01:03:15.182 --> 01:03:17.619
[sobbing]

01:03:18.751 --> 01:03:21.188
Baby, what's the matter?

01:03:22.886 --> 01:03:24.365
[Natalie]
I know.

01:03:24.409 --> 01:03:26.498
I know what happened that night.

01:03:26.541 --> 01:03:28.108
I remembered.

01:03:28.152 --> 01:03:31.198
It was me, I did it.

01:03:31.242 --> 01:03:32.286
[Annie]
Oh.

01:03:34.288 --> 01:03:36.421
I'm so sorry.

01:03:36.464 --> 01:03:37.988
I was hoping
you'd never find out.

01:03:38.031 --> 01:03:39.076
[Natalie]
Why?

01:03:39.119 --> 01:03:40.686
Why would you do that?

01:03:40.729 --> 01:03:42.383
Because they were gonna
lock you up

01:03:42.427 --> 01:03:43.558
in some horrible cell.

01:03:43.602 --> 01:03:44.864
I couldn't have that.

01:03:44.908 --> 01:03:48.520
So you went to jail for me.

01:03:48.563 --> 01:03:50.391
[Annie]
That's what mothers do.

01:03:50.435 --> 01:03:52.611
[soft music]

01:03:52.654 --> 01:03:55.179
They protect their children
at any cost.

01:03:55.222 --> 01:03:56.876
♪ ♪

01:03:56.920 --> 01:03:59.923
You were so little.

01:03:59.966 --> 01:04:02.577
But you had such a big temper.

01:04:02.621 --> 01:04:04.971
I'm gonna turn myself in.

01:04:05.015 --> 01:04:06.364
I have to.

01:04:06.407 --> 01:04:09.584
Before I hurt anyone else.

01:04:09.628 --> 01:04:13.588
I just wanted
some time with you.

01:04:15.112 --> 01:04:17.549
[Annie]
Oh, my poor baby!

01:04:17.592 --> 01:04:19.681
I'm scared.

01:04:19.725 --> 01:04:21.553
I know.

01:04:21.596 --> 01:04:23.903
But I'm gonna be with you,
right there.

01:04:23.947 --> 01:04:26.079
And we're gonna get you
some help.

01:04:26.123 --> 01:04:30.127
And you're not gonna do anything
unless my lawyer is there.

01:04:30.170 --> 01:04:32.738
I can't trust these cops.

01:04:32.781 --> 01:04:36.176
♪ ♪

01:04:36.220 --> 01:04:38.526
But first we need
to get you some rest.

01:04:38.570 --> 01:04:40.789
Come.

01:04:40.833 --> 01:04:42.400
We can lie down,

01:04:42.443 --> 01:04:44.358
and you can fall asleep
in my arms.

01:04:44.402 --> 01:04:45.794
[Natalie]
I can't.

01:04:45.838 --> 01:04:47.492
Well, just take
one of your pills.

01:04:47.535 --> 01:04:50.016
- It'll help you sleep.
- I don't have them anymore.

01:04:50.060 --> 01:04:52.758
- Why not?
- I threw them out.

01:04:52.801 --> 01:04:55.456
They were no good.

01:04:55.500 --> 01:04:57.110
But you need
to keep taking them.

01:04:57.154 --> 01:04:58.633
Why?

01:04:58.677 --> 01:05:01.375
They didn't stop me
from being crazy,

01:05:01.419 --> 01:05:02.855
from killing.

01:05:02.899 --> 01:05:04.552
[Annie]
Okay.

01:05:04.596 --> 01:05:08.121
Listen, we're gonna get you
some more pills.

01:05:08.165 --> 01:05:09.427
You're gonna need
your wits about you

01:05:09.470 --> 01:05:11.298
for what's coming.

01:05:11.342 --> 01:05:12.604
Okay?

01:05:12.647 --> 01:05:14.301
♪ ♪

01:05:14.345 --> 01:05:15.955
All right.

01:05:15.999 --> 01:05:19.002
But now you just need some rest.

01:05:19.045 --> 01:05:21.482
Come, lie down with me.

01:05:21.526 --> 01:05:23.528
♪ ♪

01:05:23.571 --> 01:05:25.530
There you go.

01:05:25.573 --> 01:05:28.837
Just like you were
a little girl, remember?

01:05:28.881 --> 01:05:30.927
♪ ♪

01:05:30.970 --> 01:05:32.537
I'm scared, Mom.

01:05:32.580 --> 01:05:34.234
♪ ♪

01:05:34.278 --> 01:05:35.496
[Annie]
I know.

01:05:35.540 --> 01:05:37.368
♪ ♪

01:05:37.411 --> 01:05:39.674
But Mommy's gonna take care
of everything.

01:05:39.718 --> 01:05:41.894
♪ ♪

01:05:41.938 --> 01:05:43.678
Get some rest.

01:05:43.722 --> 01:05:49.162
♪ ♪

01:05:53.210 --> 01:05:55.908
[distant truck horn blowing]

01:06:04.786 --> 01:06:06.049
Mom?

01:06:33.728 --> 01:06:35.817
[calm music]

01:06:35.861 --> 01:06:39.038
♪ ♪

01:06:39.082 --> 01:06:40.648
[sighing]

01:06:40.692 --> 01:06:50.744
♪ ♪

01:06:50.745 --> 01:07:03.019
♪ ♪

01:07:03.062 --> 01:07:04.281
D?

01:07:04.324 --> 01:07:07.545
♪ ♪

01:07:07.588 --> 01:07:09.329
Desmond?

01:07:09.373 --> 01:07:23.561
♪ ♪

01:07:23.604 --> 01:07:26.129
Oh my god.

01:07:26.172 --> 01:07:30.829
[Dr. Welk]
Here's a refill
so you don't run out.

01:07:30.872 --> 01:07:32.744
Dr. Welk?

01:07:32.787 --> 01:07:35.529
Does my mom write
a lot of letters?

01:07:35.573 --> 01:07:38.054
[prison official]
Writes 'em, gets 'em.

01:07:38.097 --> 01:07:40.447
A lot of these women
have pen pals.

01:07:40.491 --> 01:07:42.145
Some even come visit.

01:07:42.188 --> 01:07:45.104
Most of the time
it's just sickos

01:07:45.148 --> 01:07:48.542
who just wanna hear
about what they did.

01:07:48.586 --> 01:07:50.718
[exhaling]

01:07:50.762 --> 01:07:53.156
[eerie music]

01:07:53.199 --> 01:07:58.377
♪ ♪

01:07:58.378 --> 01:08:03.209
♪ ♪

01:09:05.314 --> 01:09:06.577
[cell phone dinging]

01:09:06.620 --> 01:09:16.673
♪ ♪

01:09:16.674 --> 01:09:21.679
♪ ♪

01:09:21.721 --> 01:09:23.332
Um, Dr. Welk!

01:09:23.376 --> 01:09:24.508
[Dr. Welk]
Oh!

01:09:24.551 --> 01:09:26.031
[Geoff]
Hi.

01:09:26.073 --> 01:09:29.469
Um, my name's Geoff.

01:09:29.513 --> 01:09:32.777
I'm a friend
of Natalie Weaver's.

01:09:32.819 --> 01:09:36.084
[Dr. Welk]
Ah, right, she's mentioned you.

01:09:36.127 --> 01:09:38.261
[indistinct conversation]

01:09:38.304 --> 01:09:41.654
♪ ♪

01:09:41.698 --> 01:09:43.917
[Geoff]
Do you have a minute to talk?

01:09:43.962 --> 01:09:46.834
About Natalie?

01:09:46.877 --> 01:09:49.794
♪ ♪

01:09:49.837 --> 01:09:52.710
[Dr. Welk]
All right, come on.

01:09:52.752 --> 01:09:55.756
I prefer to see patients
in my office, so we should...

01:09:55.800 --> 01:09:58.063
[indistinct conversation]

01:09:58.106 --> 01:10:10.336
♪ ♪

01:10:10.380 --> 01:10:12.599
[Geoff]
I'm just...

01:10:12.643 --> 01:10:15.123
really worried.

01:10:15.167 --> 01:10:20.825
♪ ♪

01:10:20.868 --> 01:10:22.479
[Natalie]
What the hell?

01:10:22.522 --> 01:10:24.263
Daniel Sturman?

01:10:24.307 --> 01:10:32.532
♪ ♪

01:10:32.576 --> 01:10:34.142
[drawer slamming]

01:10:34.186 --> 01:10:35.840
♪ ♪

01:10:35.883 --> 01:10:37.885
[Dr. Welk]
Excuse me.

01:10:37.929 --> 01:10:39.104
I'm...

01:10:39.147 --> 01:10:44.457
♪ ♪

01:10:44.501 --> 01:10:46.720
I should go.

01:10:46.764 --> 01:10:48.853
I don't wanna take up
any more of your time.

01:10:48.896 --> 01:10:54.032
♪ ♪

01:10:54.075 --> 01:10:55.120
[Dr. Welk]
Young man?

01:10:55.163 --> 01:11:03.476
♪ ♪

01:11:03.520 --> 01:11:05.913
My card, so you can make
an appointment.

01:11:05.957 --> 01:11:08.742
Clearly you're undergoing
a great amount of stress.

01:11:12.920 --> 01:11:15.227
[soft music]

01:11:15.271 --> 01:11:26.282
♪ ♪

01:11:26.325 --> 01:11:29.894
[Natalie]
Geoff, what are you doing here?

01:11:29.937 --> 01:11:32.940
Keeping an eye on you
like I said I would.

01:11:32.984 --> 01:11:36.857
I'm sorry, I know
you're still mad at me, but...

01:11:39.599 --> 01:11:40.905
Or not.

01:11:42.385 --> 01:11:44.735
Thank you, and I'm sorry

01:11:44.778 --> 01:11:47.346
for what I said,
for accusing you.

01:11:47.390 --> 01:11:49.566
It was kinda flattering

01:11:49.609 --> 01:11:52.438
thinking I was badass enough
to be a killer

01:11:52.482 --> 01:11:54.266
for a second.

01:11:54.310 --> 01:11:55.789
Okay, well, if you hear
anything from her

01:11:55.833 --> 01:11:57.835
or learn anything,
will you please give me a call?

01:11:57.878 --> 01:11:58.923
Thank you.

01:11:58.966 --> 01:12:00.098
[doorbell ringing]

01:12:00.141 --> 01:12:01.099
Natalie.

01:12:03.623 --> 01:12:05.538
- Captain.
- This is a warrant

01:12:05.582 --> 01:12:07.453
for Natalie's arrest.

01:12:09.237 --> 01:12:11.152
Natalie's not here.

01:12:11.196 --> 01:12:13.372
[Captain Lawrence]
Caroline, step aside.

01:12:13.416 --> 01:12:14.765
You're in enough trouble already

01:12:14.808 --> 01:12:17.202
lying about
Natalie's whereabouts.

01:12:17.245 --> 01:12:20.988
[suspenseful music]

01:12:21.032 --> 01:12:25.079
Natalie,
this is Captain Lawrence.

01:12:25.123 --> 01:12:26.820
Come out where we can see you.

01:12:26.864 --> 01:12:35.046
♪ ♪

01:12:35.089 --> 01:12:36.830
[cell phone buzzing]

01:12:36.874 --> 01:12:39.050
♪ ♪

01:12:39.093 --> 01:12:40.356
[Geoff]
Oh, my God.

01:12:40.399 --> 01:12:42.183
♪ ♪

01:12:42.227 --> 01:12:44.882
Come on,
I'll explain everything.

01:12:44.925 --> 01:12:50.888
♪ ♪

01:12:50.931 --> 01:12:52.237
[Captain Lawrence]
Where is she?

01:12:52.280 --> 01:12:54.587
I don't know.

01:12:54.631 --> 01:12:57.416
[Captain Lawrence]
And I'm doubting you'd tell me
if you did.

01:12:57.460 --> 01:12:58.983
Put out an APB on her,

01:12:59.026 --> 01:13:00.288
and put a trace
on her cell phone,

01:13:00.332 --> 01:13:02.943
she can't be very far away.

01:13:02.987 --> 01:13:05.076
I know you think
you're protecting her,

01:13:05.119 --> 01:13:06.947
but you're only making it worse.

01:13:06.991 --> 01:13:17.654
♪ ♪

01:13:21.005 --> 01:13:23.442
[Geoff]
So, Welk was visiting your mom

01:13:23.486 --> 01:13:25.313
using a fake identity

01:13:25.357 --> 01:13:28.316
and writing her love letters?

01:13:28.360 --> 01:13:29.317
[Natalie]
Look at these.

01:13:29.361 --> 01:13:31.102
The handwriting is identical.

01:13:31.145 --> 01:13:32.973
That's not a coincidence.

01:13:33.017 --> 01:13:35.498
He must've gotten her
to talk about the murders,

01:13:35.541 --> 01:13:37.761
things only someone who was
there that night would know.

01:13:37.804 --> 01:13:40.981
And then he imitated them
to get her paroled.

01:13:41.025 --> 01:13:42.766
[Geoff]
Why would he do that?

01:13:42.809 --> 01:13:45.333
[Natalie]
So they could be together?

01:13:45.377 --> 01:13:47.161
So when he came
to speak at the school

01:13:47.205 --> 01:13:48.641
and offered his services...

01:13:48.685 --> 01:13:50.034
[Natalie]
He was targeting me.

01:13:50.077 --> 01:13:52.950
All this time, he set me up.

01:13:52.993 --> 01:13:54.647
Think about it, my nightmares

01:13:54.691 --> 01:13:56.170
and sleepwalking
have gotten worse

01:13:56.214 --> 01:13:58.216
since I started taking
the medication.

01:13:58.259 --> 01:14:00.566
Medication he prescribed.

01:14:00.610 --> 01:14:03.221
But I haven't done it
the past couple of nights.

01:14:03.264 --> 01:14:05.223
[Geoff]
'Cause you stopped taking them.

01:14:05.266 --> 01:14:06.659
[Natalie]
The night he found me
sleepwalking,

01:14:06.703 --> 01:14:08.400
the night Kent was murdered,

01:14:08.444 --> 01:14:11.969
what was he doing out
at that hour?

01:14:12.012 --> 01:14:13.797
So Welk killed Kent.

01:14:13.840 --> 01:14:15.146
[Natalie]
And Owen.

01:14:15.189 --> 01:14:16.843
And framed me for it.

01:14:16.887 --> 01:14:18.366
We've gotta show this to police!

01:14:18.410 --> 01:14:19.585
[Natalie]
No, we can't.

01:14:19.629 --> 01:14:20.847
I stole this.

01:14:20.891 --> 01:14:23.894
I'm their prime suspect.

01:14:23.937 --> 01:14:26.853
I go there, they'll arrest me.

01:14:26.897 --> 01:14:29.116
They're already looking for me.

01:14:29.160 --> 01:14:31.902
[cell phone ringing]

01:14:31.945 --> 01:14:33.120
It's your aunt.

01:14:33.164 --> 01:14:35.645
[soft music]

01:14:35.688 --> 01:14:37.647
- Hello?
- Natalie!

01:14:37.690 --> 01:14:40.127
- Where are you?
- I'm with Geoff.

01:14:40.171 --> 01:14:42.652
Listen, I think Dr. Welk
is behind all of this.

01:14:42.695 --> 01:14:45.829
- What?
- I've got proof!

01:14:45.872 --> 01:14:48.396
[Caroline]
Listen, Natalie,
the police are looking for you

01:14:48.440 --> 01:14:51.051
and they are tracing your phone.

01:14:51.095 --> 01:14:52.488
[Geoff]
Look.

01:14:52.531 --> 01:14:55.186
♪ ♪

01:14:55.229 --> 01:14:57.144
[Natalie]
Aunt Caroline,
we'll call you back.

01:14:57.188 --> 01:15:04.717
♪ ♪

01:15:04.761 --> 01:15:06.545
- Where's he going?
- I don't know,

01:15:06.589 --> 01:15:08.634
but we should follow him
and find out.

01:15:08.678 --> 01:15:18.730
♪ ♪

01:15:18.731 --> 01:15:29.829
♪ ♪

01:15:29.873 --> 01:15:32.310
[Geoff]
What's he doing?

01:15:32.353 --> 01:15:35.008
[eerie music]

01:15:35.052 --> 01:15:40.230
♪ ♪

01:15:40.231 --> 01:15:45.062
♪ ♪

01:16:06.866 --> 01:16:08.651
[gasping]

01:16:08.694 --> 01:16:11.262
Where would you go,
Natalie, huh?

01:16:11.305 --> 01:16:25.493
♪ ♪

01:16:25.537 --> 01:16:27.365
[sirens blaring]

01:16:27.408 --> 01:16:31.543
♪ ♪

01:16:31.587 --> 01:16:32.979
Shut off the engine
and throw your keys

01:16:33.023 --> 01:16:34.851
out of the car!

01:16:34.894 --> 01:16:41.335
♪ ♪

01:16:41.379 --> 01:16:43.250
Did I do something wrong,
officer?

01:16:43.294 --> 01:16:44.687
Where's Natalie?

01:16:44.730 --> 01:16:47.690
♪ ♪

01:16:47.733 --> 01:16:51.258
[giggling]

01:16:51.302 --> 01:16:55.175
[lips smacking]

01:16:55.219 --> 01:16:57.395
[moaning]

01:16:57.438 --> 01:17:00.180
♪ ♪

01:17:00.224 --> 01:17:01.747
[Dr. Welk]
Is this where they died?

01:17:01.791 --> 01:17:03.009
- No.
- No?

01:17:03.053 --> 01:17:04.881
- In the bedroom.
- Okay, let's...

01:17:04.924 --> 01:17:06.186
Mom?

01:17:06.230 --> 01:17:08.580
[Dr. Welk]
Oh, geez, Natalie.

01:17:08.624 --> 01:17:11.365
The police... the police
are looking for you.

01:17:11.409 --> 01:17:13.237
[Annie]
Oh, come on.

01:17:13.280 --> 01:17:15.805
She knows.

01:17:15.848 --> 01:17:18.285
Idiot. I told you she was smart.

01:17:18.329 --> 01:17:20.244
You killed Owen.

01:17:20.287 --> 01:17:22.725
And Kent!

01:17:22.768 --> 01:17:24.683
[panting]

01:17:24.727 --> 01:17:28.644
[ominous music]

01:17:28.687 --> 01:17:31.647
[screaming]

01:17:31.690 --> 01:17:40.046
♪ ♪

01:17:40.090 --> 01:17:41.744
[Natalie]
Why?

01:17:41.787 --> 01:17:44.355
[Dr. Welk]
So we could be together.

01:17:44.398 --> 01:17:45.791
It was the only way.

01:17:45.835 --> 01:17:47.837
♪ ♪

01:17:47.880 --> 01:17:50.187
Your mother told me
all about you.

01:17:50.230 --> 01:17:52.406
About the night terrors
and the sleepwalking

01:17:52.450 --> 01:17:55.105
you experienced as a child.

01:17:55.148 --> 01:17:57.716
It was perfect.

01:17:57.760 --> 01:18:00.850
So, together, we planned

01:18:00.893 --> 01:18:02.678
and I acted.

01:18:02.721 --> 01:18:09.423
♪ ♪

01:18:09.467 --> 01:18:12.252
How could you do this?

01:18:12.296 --> 01:18:13.732
I'm your daughter.

01:18:13.776 --> 01:18:15.342
Exactly.

01:18:15.386 --> 01:18:16.909
♪ ♪

01:18:16.953 --> 01:18:19.956
My own flesh and blood

01:18:19.999 --> 01:18:22.785
testified against me,

01:18:22.828 --> 01:18:26.484
got me locked up in that cage.

01:18:26.527 --> 01:18:31.750
You took my life from me.

01:18:31.794 --> 01:18:36.146
And now, I'm just
returning the favor.

01:18:36.189 --> 01:18:37.669
So now what?

01:18:37.713 --> 01:18:40.193
This was not part of the plan.

01:18:40.237 --> 01:18:45.503
♪ ♪

01:18:45.546 --> 01:18:46.896
[Annie]
Oh, Natalie!

01:18:46.939 --> 01:18:49.681
Wait, stop, what is she doing?

01:18:49.725 --> 01:18:51.727
[grunting]

01:18:51.770 --> 01:18:53.903
♪ ♪

01:18:53.946 --> 01:18:56.296
Obviously she had every reason
to come after you,

01:18:56.340 --> 01:18:57.820
since you went to the police.

01:18:57.863 --> 01:19:00.126
♪ ♪

01:19:00.170 --> 01:19:01.345
Oh, well.

01:19:01.388 --> 01:19:03.129
♪ ♪

01:19:03.173 --> 01:19:06.567
That's the problem with shrinks.

01:19:06.611 --> 01:19:10.397
They think they're
the smartest person in the room.

01:19:10.441 --> 01:19:13.096
You're a monster.

01:19:13.139 --> 01:19:16.403
No, honey, you are.

01:19:16.447 --> 01:19:18.188
[panting]

01:19:18.231 --> 01:19:19.842
[rattling]

01:19:19.885 --> 01:19:28.546
♪ ♪

01:19:31.941 --> 01:19:34.160
[suspenseful music]

01:19:34.204 --> 01:19:44.736
♪ ♪

01:19:44.780 --> 01:19:47.739
There's nowhere for you
to hide from me, baby.

01:19:47.783 --> 01:19:57.792
♪ ♪

01:19:57.793 --> 01:20:04.451
♪ ♪

01:20:04.495 --> 01:20:06.236
Predictable.

01:20:06.279 --> 01:20:16.332
♪ ♪

01:20:16.333 --> 01:20:30.651
♪ ♪

01:20:30.695 --> 01:20:32.828
[grunting]

01:20:32.871 --> 01:20:42.880
♪ ♪

01:20:42.881 --> 01:20:49.757
♪ ♪

01:20:49.801 --> 01:20:51.934
[panting]

01:20:51.977 --> 01:20:55.024
♪ ♪

01:20:55.067 --> 01:20:56.025
[Caroline]
Natalie!

01:20:56.068 --> 01:20:58.331
♪ ♪

01:20:58.375 --> 01:20:59.463
[knocking]

01:20:59.506 --> 01:21:00.856
Natalie!

01:21:00.899 --> 01:21:02.335
[huffing]

01:21:02.379 --> 01:21:12.431
♪ ♪

01:21:12.432 --> 01:21:20.310
♪ ♪

01:21:20.353 --> 01:21:21.572
Natalie?

01:21:21.615 --> 01:21:23.922
[grunting]

01:21:23.966 --> 01:21:29.928
♪ ♪

01:21:29.972 --> 01:21:31.321
This is like everything
I could ask for.

01:21:31.364 --> 01:21:32.800
It's like Christmas!

01:21:32.844 --> 01:21:38.894
♪ ♪

01:21:38.937 --> 01:21:40.504
I remember now.

01:21:40.547 --> 01:21:42.027
It was you.

01:21:42.071 --> 01:21:43.942
You killed them.

01:21:43.986 --> 01:21:45.813
And you tried to blame it on me.

01:21:45.857 --> 01:21:46.989
Well, somebody had to be guilty.

01:21:47.032 --> 01:21:57.085
♪ ♪

01:21:57.086 --> 01:22:03.701
♪ ♪

01:22:03.744 --> 01:22:05.137
Mommy?

01:22:05.181 --> 01:22:10.360
♪ ♪

01:22:10.403 --> 01:22:12.449
[Annie]
Hey, sweetie.

01:22:12.492 --> 01:22:14.364
We're just playing a game here.

01:22:14.407 --> 01:22:15.669
Everything's okay.

01:22:15.713 --> 01:22:20.936
♪ ♪

01:22:20.979 --> 01:22:22.502
What are you doing?

01:22:22.546 --> 01:22:24.591
What are you doing?
Give me that back!

01:22:24.635 --> 01:22:26.985
Why did you do it?

01:22:27.029 --> 01:22:28.726
Why did you kill the Millers?

01:22:28.769 --> 01:22:31.903
Because I was sick of them
always being around,

01:22:31.947 --> 01:22:34.514
always paying
so much attention to you,

01:22:34.558 --> 01:22:37.691
pretending that
you were their daughter,

01:22:37.735 --> 01:22:39.998
acting like
they were better than me,

01:22:40.042 --> 01:22:42.348
and you playing along with it.

01:22:42.392 --> 01:22:43.654
It's all right!

01:22:43.697 --> 01:22:45.047
Mommy's here!

01:22:45.090 --> 01:22:47.440
♪ ♪

01:22:47.484 --> 01:22:50.095
Oh, don't cry, baby!

01:22:50.139 --> 01:22:52.837
Take my hand.

01:22:52.880 --> 01:22:55.971
Mommy's gonna fix everything.

01:22:56.014 --> 01:22:59.887
That's my good girl.

01:22:59.931 --> 01:23:02.194
Give Mommy the cleaver.

01:23:02.238 --> 01:23:05.154
Oh my!

01:23:05.197 --> 01:23:07.460
What a mess we've got here.

01:23:07.504 --> 01:23:12.813
♪ ♪

01:23:12.857 --> 01:23:14.337
You think the police
are gonna believe

01:23:14.380 --> 01:23:16.165
I did this, too?

01:23:16.208 --> 01:23:17.905
Oh.

01:23:17.949 --> 01:23:21.039
She... she just went crazy.

01:23:21.083 --> 01:23:23.737
She... she killed the shrink

01:23:23.781 --> 01:23:27.654
and she killed
poor Aunt Caroline.

01:23:27.698 --> 01:23:29.874
And then she tried to kill me.

01:23:29.917 --> 01:23:31.745
♪ ♪

01:23:31.789 --> 01:23:34.748
I could barely defend myself.

01:23:34.792 --> 01:23:38.709
Stop! Don't come any closer!

01:23:38.752 --> 01:23:41.929
- Stay back!
- What?

01:23:41.973 --> 01:23:43.627
You're gonna have to make me.

01:23:43.670 --> 01:23:46.021
♪ ♪

01:23:46.064 --> 01:23:47.544
Do it.

01:23:47.587 --> 01:23:50.112
I said stop!

01:23:50.155 --> 01:23:52.679
Prove that you're my daughter.

01:23:52.723 --> 01:23:55.247
♪ ♪

01:23:55.291 --> 01:23:56.422
No.

01:23:56.466 --> 01:23:58.424
♪ ♪

01:23:58.468 --> 01:24:00.035
I'm nothing like you.

01:24:00.078 --> 01:24:03.255
♪ ♪

01:24:03.299 --> 01:24:06.302
[grunting, gunshot]

01:24:06.345 --> 01:24:07.694
[Captain Lawrence]
Don't move!

01:24:07.738 --> 01:24:09.783
Put your hands
where I can see them.

01:24:09.827 --> 01:24:12.525
♪ ♪

01:24:12.569 --> 01:24:14.005
[Natalie]
Aunt Caroline.

01:24:14.049 --> 01:24:15.398
I've got you.

01:24:15.441 --> 01:24:20.316
♪ ♪

01:24:20.359 --> 01:24:22.318
[Captain Lawrence]
Officer 25, code three.

01:24:22.361 --> 01:24:23.884
I repeat, code three.

01:24:23.928 --> 01:24:25.364
We have shots fired.

01:24:25.408 --> 01:24:27.192
Suspect down and in custody.

01:24:27.236 --> 01:24:28.628
We have one adult female

01:24:28.672 --> 01:24:30.630
and one adult male casualty.

01:24:30.674 --> 01:24:34.460
Address is 4651 West Highland,
Ridgeside.

01:24:34.504 --> 01:24:38.551
I repeat, 4651 West Highland.

01:24:38.595 --> 01:24:40.423
[radio dispatcher]
Copy that, ambulance dispatched

01:24:40.466 --> 01:24:42.903
to 4651 West Highland.

01:24:42.947 --> 01:24:45.297
[soft music]

01:24:45.341 --> 01:24:47.125
[Geoff]
Nat, are you okay?

01:24:47.169 --> 01:24:48.648
[Natalie]
I am, I'm good.

01:24:48.692 --> 01:24:50.781
[Geoff]
And your mom, she...

01:24:50.824 --> 01:24:53.131
[Natalie]
She's right here.

01:24:53.175 --> 01:25:03.227
♪ ♪

01:25:03.228 --> 01:25:12.977
♪ ♪

01:25:14.848 --> 01:25:17.547
[mellow music]

01:25:17.590 --> 01:25:22.768
♪ ♪

01:25:22.769 --> 01:25:27.600
♪ ♪

01:25:56.107 --> 01:25:58.283
[cheerful music]

01:25:58.327 --> 01:26:01.634
♪ ♪

01:26:01.678 --> 01:26:04.507
[whirring]

01:26:04.550 --> 01:26:06.639
[upbeat music]

01:26:06.683 --> 01:26:12.689
♪ ♪

01:26:12.732 --> 01:26:13.603
[whistling music]
